title: chili mac
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to meat.
In a large pot, add tomatoes and kidney beans; break up tomatoes.
Add meat and onion.
Use chili powder to taste.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Take spaghetti (about 1 handful), break into thirds, add to pot.
Cook until spaghetti is done.

title: hidden valley crackers
directions: Mix Wesson oil, Hidden Valley dressing mix, lemon-pepper, garlic salt or powder and dill weed.
Pour over oyster or soup crackers.
Set aside overnight.
Keep in Ziploc bag.

title: favorite beef loaf
directions: Combine all
ingredients and mix well.	Shape into loaf and bake in pan
or
x
x 2-inch pan.
Can use deer and sausage meat, equal
part
deer
burger (1 package) or 1 pound sausage meat and
1 beaten egg, 8 ounces tomato catsup and 1/2 package meat
loaf	seasoning, onions, green peppers, carrot, cracker crumbs and salt.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces; let set in beaten egg for 1 hour or overnight.
Make into patties.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in Crisco until brown.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with mushrooms (with liquid).
Top with cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: martha's "porkcupine" meatballs
directions: Mix above ingredients and form into eight round meatballs.

title: shrimp puffs
directions: Preheat broiler.
Whip the egg white until stiff.
Fold in the cheese, salt, paprika, red pepper and mayonnaise.
Heap the mixture lightly onto crackers or rounds of toast.
Garnish each one with 1/2 shrimp.
Broil puffs until light brown.
Serve hot.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Melt oleo and saute zucchini and onion.
Stir in parsley, basil, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Combine eggs and cheese.
Stir into zucchini mixture.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; dice into about 1/2 to 1-inch squares. Cook in salted water, until just tender; drain and let cool. Dice eggs and add all other ingredients. Fold into potatoes; do not over mix. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: butterscotch zucchini bread
directions: Beat together the eggs, oil, zucchini, sugar and pudding. Add the vanilla, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and baking powder into mixture. Mix until smooth. Add nuts or raisins. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, a Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large pot, boil potatoes over medium heat for 35 to 45 minutes.
Boil eggs over medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in a microwave-safe container (2-quart size works well).
Cook together for 2 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Put 4 quarts of popcorn into a paper grocery bag.
Pour sugar mixture over popcorn.
Close bag, roll down top and shake.
Place bag in microwave.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake; microwave an additional 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Pour on cookie sheets to cool.

title: chewy peanut butter bars
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars until light.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and coconut; mix well.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: raisin nut spice cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients, then add alternately the buttermilk and dry ingredients to the shortening mixture.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared 9-inch cake pans (greased and floured).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and frost with White Butter Icing.

title: spicy snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a small bowl, blend oleo and seasoning mix.
In a large roasting pan, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour oleo mixture over snacks; stir until well coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely. Store in an airtight container.
Yields about 15 cups snack mix.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Gradually add flour. Mix thoroughly adding flour as needed for handling.
Roll on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.

title: grandma jacobs' hash brown casserole
directions: Line frozen bricks on bottom of baking pan.
Cover with the sausage.
Sprinkle onions over sausage; cover with the grated cheese.
Beat the eggs and milk together; pour this over the other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
(Can be made the night before and refrigerated under cover.)

title: pesto
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Put in blender until smooth.
Add basil; puree.
Add walnuts.
Finally, add Parmesan cheese.
Smooth on French bread.
Heat in oven at 325°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix together.
Add can of pineapple. Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: daddy's christmas punch
directions: Melt sugar in water in saucepan. Put pineapple and orange juice in punch bowl. Add sugar, water and Kool aid. Mix well. Then add Ginger ale. Mix and decorate with ice ring.

title: tina's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water.
Microwave milk for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add margarine or butter to milk and allow it to melt or at least soften.
Add water and yeast to milk and butter. Add salt, sugar and egg.
Gradually mix in flour 1 cup at a time. Let rise until double; punch down.	Divide dough in half and knead, adding just enough flour to handle well.
Roll out dough in rectangle and spread with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut in 1-inch rolls.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes.
(I usually set them on top of the oven and turn on to help them raise.)
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Use caramel or white icing.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Chill 3 or 4 hours or overnight (more crisp if chilled overnight).

title: aunt jennie's peach crisp
directions: Put peaches in a baking dish.
Mix water and lemon juice; pour over peaches.
Mix other ingredients together; put over peaches. Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 30 more minutes.
Serve with topping or ice cream.

title: microwave cheese-chili dip
directions: Place Cheez Whiz and chili in glass casserole dish.
Mix together.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted, stirring every minute.
Serve in small crock pot or fondue pot (keep dip hot). Serve with sturdy dippers, dip is very thick.

title: strawberry cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together all but strawberries, then add strawberries last.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix melted margarine with cracker crumbs and line a casserole with mixture. Reserve 1/2 cup mixture for top.
Mix 4 tablespoons butter, salt, flour, pepper, milk and grated cheese in saucepan. Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Place asparagus over crumbs in pan.
Pour cheese sauce over asparagus, then top with 1/2 cup reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut slice off top of tomato. Mix seasonings and place small amount on top of tomatoes in shallow baking pot. Dot each tomato with butter. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: beef ribs marinade
directions: Put the juice of one whole lemon on meat.
Lay onion rings on meat.
Put all other ingredients on meat and cover.
Store in refrigerator overnight or for 4 to 5 hours.
Shake and turn upside down to mix marinade a couple of times.
Cook and add barbecue sauce to taste.

title: sugar-free coca-cola salad
directions: Mix together cherry and lime jello and the crushed pineapple. Put on stove and cook until boiling water.
Take off stove and add Coke and nuts to mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Cook spinach in unsalted water per package directions or for 8 minutes in the microwave without added water. Drain.
In medium saucepan, cook carrots, onion and mushrooms in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and oregano.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound veal between 2 pieces waxed paper until thin.
Cut veal into serving pieces and coat each piece with flour.
Heat butter in skillet until it sizzles.
Add the veal and cook over high heat until browned on both sides.
Add sliced mushrooms and saute briefly.
Add beef bouillon and Marsala; swoosh everything around in pan and cook 1 minute longer.

title: old-fashioned jelly rolls
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs warm to room temperature about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease bottom of a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, then line with wax paper.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt, then set aside.
At high speed, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until very thick and light, about 5 minutes.
At low speed, blend in sifted dry ingredients and vanilla just until combined.
Turn into prepared pan; spread evenly.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until surface springs back when gently pressed with fingertips.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Combine berries, sugar, flour, salt and orange juice.
Fill pastry-lined 8-inch pie pan.
Dot with butter and adjust top crust. If desired, can sprinkle sugar over top of crust, also.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes; then turn oven to 350° and continue baking for 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: sausage and peppers italiano
directions: In covered skillet over medium heat, cook sausage in 2 tablespoons of water for 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Cook until sausage is browned on all sides.
Add green peppers, onion and garlic to sausage in skillet.
Cook until peppers are tender-crisp, stirring frequently.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, 1 cup of water and vinegar.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cauliflower frittata
directions: Bring a large saucepan of salted water to boil.
Remove the tough stalks of the cauliflower.
Separate the florets and cook for 10 minutes in the boiling water.
Drain and cool.
Heat the oil in a skillet or nonstick pan.

Add cauliflower, salt, pepper and anchovies and saute over medium-high heat for a few minutes. Beat the eggs in a small bowl; add the capers and salt and pepper. Pour this mixture over the cauliflower.
Cook until the frittata is golden on the bottom.
Invert onto a lid, then slide it back off the lid into the pan and cook the other side.
Transfer the frittata to a serving plate and serve immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Step 1:
Mix the first 3 ingredients (flour, eggs and shortening); blend with pastry cutter until meal texture.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers.
Mix in sugar, juice and nuts.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: peanut rolls
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually; add water and vanilla, then dry ingredients that have been sifted together twice.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cold, cut in small squares and spread with the following mixture:
one pound powdered sugar and 1/2 pound butter.
Roll in ground peanuts.

title: squash relish
directions: Cut up peppers, squash and onions; drain 1 hour.
Salt to taste.
Mix last 4 ingredients. Bring to boil; add squash, onions and peppers. Cook 3 minutes.
Put in jars.
Seal jars while still hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine layer of squash and butter. Add cracker crumbs and grated cheese with other ingredients until you fill Pyrex dish casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato beef stew
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook beef until browned and no longer pink, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water.
Add beans, carrots and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to simmering.
Cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown chicken and onion in oleo.
Add soup, broth and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add to cooked noodles. Mix and serve.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Measure 1/4 cup of soup, mixing in with all ingredients except mashed potatoes.
Form into a loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven; drain fat.
Spread hot mashed potatoes over meat loaf.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Heat remaining soup (you might want two cans) and serve over sliced meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix together oranges and pineapple, then add coconut, nuts, sour cream and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer all vegetables, ending with drained peas. Use any other layers you like. Mix the mayonnaise and sugar together and pour on top of salad. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and bacon.

title: shao lin jones stir-fried chicken
directions: Heat wok to high temperature.
Debone and dice chicken thighs. Boil Ramen noodles as directed on package (do not add seasoning packet yet).
Pour frozen vegetables in heated wok that has been coated with olive oil and margarine.
Stir-fry vegetables until soft, yet crunchy.
Add diced chicken seasonings and Ramen flavor packets.
Stir until fully mixed.
Lower heat to simmer.
Drain noodles, rinse and place on heated plate.
Drain wok juices and pour vegetables and chicken over noodles.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Mix altogether and freeze; put in plastic cups.

title: grandma's brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop fine.
Wash mushrooms (don't soak). Slice thin and saute in 1/4 cup oil for about 4 minutes.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is golden.
Add tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
In another frying pan, add remaining 1/4 cup oil, saute veal until lightly brown on both sides, frying a few cutlets at a time.
Return all veal to skillet.
Pour sauce and wine over veal and simmer 6 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese and serve over buttered noodles.

title: rum balls(no bake)
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly with your hands.
Form into balls.
Roll in extra amount of powdered sugar.
Let stand in an airtight container until flavor penetrates (at least 1 week).

title: stuffing for turkey
directions: Mix together and stuff in turkey.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix orange jello and cottage cheese.
Drain mandarin orange jello and pineapple, then add to cottage cheese.

title: fruit salad pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cook the sugar, flour, pineapple and fruit plus juice until thick. Add Jell-O dry.
Add bananas and pecans. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill. Serve. Top with Cool Whip.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally, until cabbage and rice are tender and all water is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add additional water in small amounts, if needed.
Good served with corn bread.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Save broth.
Tear chicken into bite size pieces and line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over chicken.
Put dry stuffing over soup.
Pour chicken broth, about 2 cups or more, over stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: nate's leftover casserole
directions: Combine at least a cup of each of the first three ingredients in a small microwave casserole dish.
Add cream of chicken soup and heat in microwave,
maybe 3 or 4 minutes. Stir halfway through.

title: broccoli casserole i
directions: Thaw broccoli in bowl.
Drain water.
Mix liquid, mushroom soup and chopped onion together.
Butter an 8-inch square casserole. Sprinkle 1/3 of broccoli in casserole.
Top with 1/3 soup mixture, 1/3 stuffing mix and 1/3 melted butter.
Repeat twice.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until hot through and bubbly in center.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's company meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into loaf and place into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles(no cook, no seal)
directions: Use any size cucumbers.
Make brine of salt and water.
Wash cukes and cover with brine water.
Use a plastic, glass or enameled container; not stainless or aluminum.
Pack as many cukes as possible in container and weight down so all will be submerged under water.
Soak 14 days.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Place sugar, cinnamon and apples into dish.
Blend brown sugar, flour and butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Spread on greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Optional frosting.

title: broiled icing
directions: Mix together and spread on top of a hot cake (9 x 13-inch). Put under broiler until it bubbles.

title: coconut balls
directions: Use double boiler.
Melt margarine and pour over (nuts) coconut, vanilla, milk and powdered sugar.
Mix well and form into small balls and set aside to chill.
Melt wax and chocolate bits. Dip balls into chocolate mixture and lay on wax paper to cool. Serve.
(Use toothpicks to dip balls into chocolate.)

title: crescent coffee cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Oven: 350°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine and mix well the first 7 ingredients, 1/2 cup cheese, garlic salt and enough milk to make a creamy mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.
Serve with a sturdy cracker. Yields 1/2 quart.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put shortening, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Pour in one-quart boiling water, stir until shortening dissolves.
Let cool to lukewarm and add beaten eggs.
Dissolve yeast in 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water.
Add to cooled shortening mix.
Add 2 cups flour at a time until stiff enough to knead on floured board. Knead 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubles.
Shape loaves into equal portions.
Let rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken savannah
directions: Mix soup mixture and barbecue sauce in large casserole dish with a top.
Roll chicken pieces to coat well with onion sauce mixture.
Place coated pieces, skin side up, in sauce.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers and 1/2 cup vinegar in a blender.
Blend well.
Add 1 cup vinegar to all ingredients except Certo.
Add red or green food coloring.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add Certo, stirring well.
Makes 6 or 7 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
If
desired, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hash brown breakfast casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns, then layer in a lightly greased 9 x 13 inch dish with browned sausage and the cheese. Combine eggs and milk, beating well. Pour over layers, bake at 350° about 50 minutes. (Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated or frozen.) Makes 12 servings.

title: mountain mud slide cake
directions: For crust, melt oleo.
Combine with flour and nuts; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown; cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Mix the flour, sugar, egg, baking powder and salt together; it will be crumbly.
Sprinkle this mixture over the apples.
On top of this sprinkle some cinnamon and pour the melted butter over all.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until apples test done.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cacciatore ala sam
directions: Brown chicken and sausage in a skillet with a little oil. Remove meat and set aside.
In same pan, saute pepper and onion until tender.
Layer chicken and sausage in a shallow roasting pan.
Top with pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over all. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with cooked spaghetti.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In butter, brown ground beef, celery and onion. Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes. Serve on buns with coleslaw.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs for 10 minutes at high speed. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and beat well.
Add flavoring and coconut and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
When cake is done, let cool in pan 5 minutes before removing.
Place under a cake cover to retain moisture. Does not freeze well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix salt, soda and flour together.
Add to mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon water, if needed to mix.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas cider
directions: Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with an orange slice.

title: pink cloud
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well for several days.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Serve and eat with Wheat Thin Crackers.

title: easy strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients.
Freeze according to your ice cream freezer directions.
Fresh strawberries may also be used.

title: broccoli devon
directions: Steam broccoli, place in greased dish. Sprinkle with cooked chicken. Mix soup and mayo together. Spread over chicken layer. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: After crushing cookies, add oleo and pat into pie pan; chill for 1 hour.
Melt marshmallows and milk over double boiler.
Let cool.
Whip cream until stiff.
Stir into marshmallow mixture.
Add creme de cacao and creme de menthe.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill for 4 hours.
Grate chocolate over top before serving.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Mix together margarine, milk, sugar and egg.
Cook over low heat until this boils.
Remove from heat and cool in refrigerator.
When cool, add coconut, chopped nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread this over crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers. Make topping.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook until candy thermometer registers 290°.
Remove from heat and stir in soda. Spread thinly onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef;
mix
all ingredients together, then simmer 45 minutes and serve.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on top of stove.
Mix milk, cream of mushroom and onion together in casserole dish.
After pork chops are brown, put into casserole with other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until pork chops are done.

title: cold senegalese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat or blend in an electric blender until creamy-smooth.
Chill.
Serve in cups or bowls.
If you like, sprinkle with chopped, toasted almonds or flaked coconut.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, nuts, confectioners sugar and margarine and put in bottom of pan.
Mix and pour together ingredients over crumb mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm.
Cool and top with 1 can blueberry pie mix and one 12-ounce Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat together for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oven baked stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from top of peppers and remove all seeds and rinse.
Cook peppers in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Cook and stir ground beef, salt and onion in skillet until onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in garlic salt, rice and 1 cup tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Stand peppers upright in 8 x 8-inch ungreased baking dish.
Stuff each pepper with 1/2 cup meat mixture.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers and bake for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: quick oats soup(lebanon)
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add meat and saute for a while.
Add water, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook until the meat is done.
Add tomato soup, oats and cilantro.
Stir well. Let cook for 15 minutes.
It is done!
Some lemon juice with the soup makes it taste better.
Makes enough for 8 people.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef in thin strips.
Cook over medium heat the oil, beef and garlic until beef is brown.
Add onion.
Stir often.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown garlic in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with sauce and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole (greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Layer meat and dressing mix in casserole. Mix soup, broth and herbs.
Pour
over meat and cook for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in roaster. Brown hamburger and bacon. Crumble in beans. Add onion, brown sugar, catsup, salt and vinegar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix cheeses and bread crumbs together, in a bowl wide enough for chicken. Dip chicken in melted butter, then into bread crumb mixture, roll until covered. Place in baking dish (seam side down). Sprinkle remaining mixture over chicken. Then drizzle 1\3 cup (1\2 butter, 1\2 water) over chicken. Bake at 325° for 45 min. covered, uncover and bake for 15 more min.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream flour, oleo, and sugar. Add spices. Beat eggs until fluffy. Add buttermilk and eggs and mix well. Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour. Makes about 8 loaves. Grease pans and fill 1/2 full.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic in butter; add tortellini and chicken broth and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add spinach, basil and stewed tomatoes and simmer.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: molasses whipped cream
directions: Combine and whip.
Delicious served on warm gingerbread or other warm spice cake.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter and spread graham cracker crumbs evenly.
Pour approximately 1/3 of the sweet milk evenly over crumbs.
Layer evenly chocolate chips, coconut and nuts over crumbs.
Pour remaining sweet milk evenly over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool before cutting.

title: rhea's reuben sandwiches
directions: Night before needed, mix drained kraut, mayonnaise and dill weed.
Stir; cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, stir well as liquid accumulates in bowl.
Open corned beef, heat in microwave safe bowl until warm and spreadable (may need to add 1/4 to 1/2 cup mayonnaise).
Spread beef on rye, top with kraut mixture then Swiss cheese.
If heating on grill or skillet, butter rye (or you can microwave for heating).

title: kitchen floor pickles
directions: Use small to medium-size cucumbers. Chunk up cucumbers and pack tightly in a gallon jar (glass or plastic). Add remaining ingredients. Fill the rest of the way with water. Cap and let set for 1 month. Remove from jar and wash cucumbers and jar. Put back in jar. Add 5 cups sugar. Cap and shake jar until cucumbers are covered with juice. Pickles are ready to eat. They do not have to be refrigerated.

title: hot mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl; stir well.
Store mix in an airtight container.
For each serving, place 3 tablespoons in cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Yields 75 servings.

title: chicken eva
directions: Brush chicken breasts with lemon juice, then roll in seasoned cracker crumbs.
Brown in skillet.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Mix together in saucepan on low heat cream of chicken soup, butter and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry-pineapple homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with an electric mixer.
Pour in freezer can and add whole milk to fill line.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread in 8 x 8 baking serving dish in order given. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with corn chips.

title: california stir-fry
directions: Prepare taco shells.
Heat butter in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Stir in cornstarch.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir over low heat until hot, about 5 minutes.
Stir in beef, raisins and salt; cook and stir until beef and raisins are hot, about 5 minutes.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of beef mixture into each taco shell.
Yields 5 servings.

title: broccoli casserole with the ritz
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain water.
Add 1/2 stick margarine and cubed Velveeta.
Mix and pour into casserole dish. Crush crackers and mix with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer until smooth.
Chill.

title: southern catfish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly spray a baking dish with vegetable oil spray.
Sprinkle fillets with black pepper.
Set aside.

In a shallow dish, combine cornmeal, parsley and cayenne pepper. Dip fillets in milk mixture and then roll in cornmeal mixture. Place fillets in prepared baking dish and bake 15 to 17 minutes or until done.
Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.

title: flapper pudding
directions: Spread half of vanilla wafer crumbs on bottom of 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cream butter; gradually add confectioners sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat 1 minute more.
Fold in egg whites (mixture may look curdled); beat at medium speed for a few seconds or until smooth.
Fold in pineapple and nuts. Carefully spread mixture over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs. Chill until firm, 5 hours or overnight.
Cut in 10 squares. Garnish with cherries.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears.
Place each pear half on lettuce leaf.
Place 1 teaspoon mayonnaise on each pear.
Top with grated cheese and a cherry.
Chill until serving.

title: chocolate vinegar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Make 3 indentations with a spoon in dry mix.
Add 1 liquid to each indentation.
Pour water over all; mix well.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt butter, 1 egg and lemon cake mix all together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and whole box of sugar.
Pour over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Sift more sugar over the top.

title: jello salad - lime
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in a bowl and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add pineapple, cottage cheese, evaporated milk, mayonnaise and chopped nuts.
Mix together with a spoon.
Let harden (preferred overnight).

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat soup, Cheez Whiz, chili powder and garlic. Pour over hominy and onions, bake at 350° for 30 minutes or cook in microwave for 5 minutes or so.
Take out of oven or microwave and add crushed Fritos on top.

title: roasted lamb chops with cognac mustard
directions: Melt the butter with the garlic and rosemary over low heat. let stand for 10 minutes to absorb flavor.	Brush this over the lamb chops, then season with salt and pepper.
Arrange single layered in a baking pan.
Roast the lamb chops at 450° for 10 minutes, then mix Cognac and mustard and baste chops. Continue roasting until done, about 5 more minutes.	Serves 8.

title: salmon corn chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large, heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually add 1 cup broth.
Stir until boiling and thickened.
Stir in remaining broth, half and half, corn, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, but do not boil. Remove from heat.
Add salmon.

title: cabbage surprise
directions: Cook the cabbage and apple in boiling water until soft.
When they are soft, drain off the water.
Put in the raisins and stir together.

title: rainbow sherbet pie
directions: *Sliced strawberries, kiwi fruit, oranges, blueberries, blackberries and raspberries.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Prepare broccoli. Combine macaroni and cheese, cut up broccoli, ham, onion, soup and milk.
Season to taste.
Microwave on High 10 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and microwave until cheese is melted.

title: debbie's cheese ball
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk.
Boil 2 minutes; stir constantly.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; mix well.
Drop on wax paper.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
In a large stockpot, cover beans with water to within 3-inches of top of pot.
Cook on medium heat approximately 3 hours or until beans are soft.

title: fifth sunday breakfast pizza
directions: Divide flaky biscuits into 2 layers each.
Begin in the middle of a large pizza pan.
Place biscuit layers close together to fill pan. Pat gaps together.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs with softened cream cheese.
Spoon egg mixture over biscuit crust.
Sprinkle cheese over entire pizza.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until edge is lightly browned and center is set.
Cut into wedges or squares.
Serves 8 as main dish, 12 as appetizer.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat the ingredients about 2 minutes, then add the eggs, one at a time.
Grease and flour a tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine over low heat in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over margarine. Arrange pineapple halves and cherries in pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed and pour over fruit in pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes. Invert at once onto foil covered baking sheet.
Leave pan over cake for few minutes; remove pan.

title: raspberry preserves cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Mix in 1/2 cup preserves.
Blend well.
Add sour cream and then eggs.
Beat well. Blend together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add gradually to first mixture, beating well.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cook in microwave on full power for 4 to 5 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly pressed with finger (you may want to turn dish halfway through cooking time).
Cool and spread with 1/2 cup preserves, whipped cream or Raspberry Frosting.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat the whipping cream and sugar until foamy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat.
Fill ice cream freezer 3/4 full and add whole milk to fill full.
Put in your electric ice cream freezer.
Add ice all around in container. Sprinkle salt over ice and make ice cream.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Add nuts, raisins and apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: velvet custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, salt and vanilla and mix.
Add scalded milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Check center with table knife.
It will come out clean when done.

title: shrimp squiggle
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add shrimp and soup last.
Heat thoroughly (saute until pink).
Serve over spaghetti.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat milk in medium saucepan. Cut Velveeta into small pieces and add to hot milk; stir until cheese melts. Add Parmesan and salt.
Then add macaroni.

title: artichoke dip(microwave)
directions: Drain and finely chop artichokes.
Mix with cheese and mayonnaise.
Microwave on High 5 to 8 minutes, stirring once, until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll mixture into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Place in oven for 1 minute.
Take out and smash a crisscross pattern with a fork.
Bake an additional 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cheesy lima beans
directions: Drain beans; mix beans and liquid, celery, onion powder, pepper, mayonnaise and 1/2 cup grated cheese in a bowl.
Put ingredients into a greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and spread crushed crackers over all.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in oil using Dutch oven.
Remove pork chops. Add rice and brown slightly, stirring constantly.
Add water and place pork chops on top of rice.
Cook in oven at 400°
about 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: steak cooked in beer
directions: Mix all ingredients and put over chopped steak in a casserole dish and add other mixture.
Bake for about 1/2 to 1 hour.
It is real good and better the next day.

title: tennessee fried corn
directions: Cut grains not too close to cob; scrape the rest off the cob. Add 1/2 cup of water, salt and sugar to skillet and cook about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: johnnie mazzetti
directions: Fry hamburger meat and onion together, then mix mushroom soup, tomato sauce and cheese.
Mix all together and pour over noodles.

title: swedish pecan balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except powdered sugar and mix well. Shape dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 275° for about 30 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again after cookies have cooled.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square pan with non-stick coating.
In bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat margarine until fluffy.
Gradually add brown and granulated sugars, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in egg substitute and dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla, apples, applesauce and nuts.
Spread mixture into prepared pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain on paper towel.
Crumble.
Saute onion and celery in 1/2 cup of drippings.
Combine sugar, flour and seasonings.
Stir into drippings.
Add vinegar and water, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and bacon bits.
Mix thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain water from artichokes.
Cut in small pieces, cut cheese in bits.
Add mayonnaise and salt; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread on crackers.

title: double berry frost
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth and frothy, about 1 minute.
Pour into cups.

title: wake-up casserole
directions: Place croutons in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese and mushrooms.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain and spread over cheese layer.
Beat eggs with 2 cups of milk and seasonings; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
(May be frozen at this point.)
Mix soup with 1/2 cup milk and spread on top before baking.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Mix sugar, stick of oleo, Crisco, buttermilk, egg yolks, flour, soda, nuts and coconut together.
Fold in egg whites.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Heat oven to 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together in one bowl the eggs, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Then add the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, sour milk and cocoa.
Add hot water to make the paste mix together.
Drop the cookies on the cookie sheet and spread apart.
Cook for 15 minutes or more.

title: home done pickled beets
directions: Cook beets.
Peel and pack in jars. Pour liquid over and seal.

title: donna's corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Dip franks into mixture and deep-fry. Do not fry too fast or they may not get done all the way.

title: mustard potato salad
directions: In a saucepan, cover potatoes with water and cook until tender, but firm. Drain and cool completely. In a bowl, combine egg salad, mayonnaise, mustard, onion and salt. Stir in potatoes; cover and chill. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 cup flour, butter, powdered sugar and salt with pastry cutter.
Pat in 8 x 8-inch greased square pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat egg with fork until well blended.
Stir in cooking oil, lemon, rind and vanilla.
Blend until mixture thickens; add sugar. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop by teaspoons about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and place into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add peaches and spread evenly.
Pour flour, sugar and milk mixture on top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges, reserving liquid.
Prepare pudding using liquid from the fruit in place of milk.
In a bowl, gently fold fruit into pudding. Chill for 2 hours.
Add bananas just before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crunchy asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, saving liquid.
Arrange in buttered casserole. Cover with egg slices and add salt and pepper.
Dilute soup with liquid from asparagus and pour over asparagus and eggs.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover with crushed corn flake crumbs.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted and casserole is thoroughly heated.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix egg, sugar, shortening, bananas and vanilla until smooth.
Sift flour and soda together.
Blend in banana mixture.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or two 7 x 3/8-inch pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and chocolate powder.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Mix well. Drop on wax paper and let cool (1 teaspoon size drops).

title: healthy whole-grain muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flours, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Blend bananas in a blender or food processor. Add margarine and continue to blend.
Combine water and raisins in a microwave-safe container and heat for 1 1/2 minutes on High. Add raisin mixture, buttermilk and walnuts to bananas and process on High until well blended.
Pour into a large mixing bowl and add brown sugar and eggs.
Mix until combined.
Add dry ingredients, oats, wheat germ and chocolate chips and mix until combined.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 36 muffins.

title: lentil stew
directions: Preheat olive oil.
Add onion, shallot and currants. Cook until onions appear glassy.
Add yams, bay leaf, lentils and chicken broth.
Simmer for 35 to 45 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. May be made a day ahead and reheated.
Serves 8.

title: orange chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add chicken and cook until browned on both sides.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms over high heat, stirring occasionally, until all liquid has evaporated.
Sprinkle mushrooms with flour and stir quickly to combine.
Gradually stir in water.
Add orange juice and broth mix; stirring occasionally, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let chicken simmer for 3 minutes.
Serve with sprinkled onions and orange sections.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Crush corn chips and spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add chili to ground beef and spread on corn chips. Slice tamales and layer on top of beef. Top with layer of cheese. Heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: punch(very good)
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; add pineapple juice, water, sugar and almond flavoring.
Freeze or use immediately.
Take out of freezer about 6 hours before you are ready to use.
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture.
Use 1 or 2 cups sherbet.
One recipe makes 30 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix with milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
In bowl, mix 1 cup milk with pudding mix until thickened.
Stir in pumpkin and spice.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and nuts, if desired.

title: sweet and sour beef and cabbage
directions: Season each layer, using in total 2 teaspoons salt (regular or seasoned) and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until it resembles crumbs. Combine slightly beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Sprinkle on dry ingredients.
Mix with fork.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Roll out or divide and put in refrigerator.
Very good for freezing. Makes 3 or 4 crusts.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage just until wilted; drain well.
Place layer of cabbage in large casserole dish.
Add half of the cheese, soup and oleo.
Repeat layers.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and light brown.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream shortening and add other ingredients, beating until the icing is a creamy smooth consistency.
If a stiffer icing is needed, add a little more confectioners sugar and if it should be a bit thinner, add a few drops of hot water.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in blender until smooth.
Remove from blender and add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Chill until very cold.
Very attractive served in hollowed out cabbage or just on platter surrounded with fresh vegetables.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars, milk, cocoa and salt in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute at low heat.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, oats and flour. Stir.
Drop on wax paper on cookie sheet. Cool!
Eat.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except onion, unless it is to be served that day.
If too dry, add 1 tablespoon each of mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and sugar.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump 1 large can crushed pineapple, 1 box yellow cake mix, 1 cup coconut and 1 cup nuts into your greased pan and mix or layer.
Cut 2 sticks of margarine into 1/2-inch squares.
Scatter butter squares on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in tomato soup, water and cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
Blend with the macaroni and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded cheese and 2 tablespoons buttered crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until dissolved and chill.
Add remaining ingredients and add ginger ale last.
Add ice ring.
Serves 100.

title: diego salad
directions: Slice onions, tomatoes, green peppers and cucumbers.
Mix remaining ingredients and add vegetables.
Marinate at least two or three hours.
Will make small bowl full.
Double or triple for larger bowl.

title: sally's chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients by hand.
Press in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chocolate frosting generously on top.
Chill.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: white flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening and mix thoroughly.
Add water and mix well.
Shape dough into egg size balls and place on floured board.
Cover with wax paper and let stand for 20 minutes. Dust board with flour and roll out dough, round and paper thin. Place on hot grill or iron skillet.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Remove and serve with meal.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients
and pour into a 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle 1 yellow cake mix and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Drizzle with melted margarine; do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves at least 12.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter.
Gradually add dry milk; mix well.
Form into balls with greased hands.
Roll in dry cereal flakes.
Chill until firm.
Makes 18 balls.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add melted chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 325° oven until center is done.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop real fine or run ingredients through food processor. Brown meat, all onions and garlic.
Cook a few minutes.
Drain. Add salt.
Roll in skins and seal with beaten egg.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Toss.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Chill to set.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put all the ingredients into a pot; remove film as it boils. Continue to boil for 1 hour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook another 1 1/2 hours.
Yummie!

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add hot milk, vanilla and cereal.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Place in a pan of hot water that comes up about halfway on the casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until a knife inserted into custard comes out clean.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: moussaka
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery, onions, 1/2 can tomato sauce, garlic and tomato paste.
Slice tomatoes.
Grate and mix cheeses.
In buttered casserole, layer as follows: eggplant, cheese, meat sauce, tomatoes, eggplant, tomatoes, other 1/2 can tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: grandma's vegetable soup
directions: Put first 4 ingredients, cleaned and chopped, into a large container or soup pot.
Match this amount with equal quantity of peeled tomatoes.
Add salt to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, but not mushy.

title: pour crust cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Add pie filling all around dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over very low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add salmon and peas.
Serve on crackers or toast.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter a small casserole dish.
Put a layer of sliced Potatoes. Sprinkle with Onion Salt, Pepper and Flour.
Dot with Butter.
Put another layer of sliced Potatoes.
Sprinkle with Celery Salt, Pepper and Flour.
Dot with Butter.
Put another layer of sliced Potatoes.
Sprinkle with Salt, Pepper and Flour.
Dot with Butter. Almost cover with Milk.
Top with Cracker Crumbs.
Bake at 350 for 1-1/4 hours.

title: chicken joseph
directions: Mix together the sour cream, soup and wine.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place chicken in single layer in pan; sprinkle with seasonings and cheese.
Top with mushrooms and soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour green beans
directions: Cook beans until just tender.
Measure liquid and add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Mix honey, vinegar, cornstarch, soy sauce, pickle and green pepper.
Bring to a boil; cook for 10 minutes, stirring until sauce thickens.
Add beans; simmer for 4 minutes.

title: becky's salmon
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon into mixing bowl.
Add milk, eggs, onion, salt, black pepper, paprika and crushed crackers.
Mix thoroughly.
Pat out into 6 to 7 patties or "tee pees."
Roll lightly in cornmeal to coat.
Place on plate and refrigerate 30 minutes or longer, covered with plastic wrap.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in jar.
Use 3 teaspoons heaped in hot water.

title: superb cheesecake
directions: Beat cottage cheese and cream cheese until thoroughly blended. Beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, then cornstarch mixed with flour, lemon peel and juice and vanilla.
Blend in melted butter and yogurt.

title: francis marion reception punch
directions: Combine orange juice, ice water, lemon juice and pineapple juice; mix thoroughly and chill.
To serve, pour half of mixture into a large punch bowl.
Add 2 quarts carbonated water or ginger ale.
Punch may be sweetened with dissolved sugar desired.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Toast rice for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper and brown in 1/4 cup hot fat.
Remove chicken, then cook onion, celery and garlic until tender.
Stir in rice and remaining ingredients.
Transfer into 11 x 7-inch dish, top with chicken breasts and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until chicken is done and rice tender.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, beaten.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together 6 times.
Add milk to beaten yolks, sugar and butter, then add flour.
Add lemon extract.
Beat all of mixture well; then fold in beaten egg whites.
Use tube pan; grease and line with oiled paper.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: duffie's elk or deer hamburgers
directions: Add
a	little water to bread to make it soft and break up into crumbs.
Combine all
ingredients.
Make
into patties and fry in frying pan.	Cook slowly.
Will be good and juicy.

title: homemade bread
directions: First make potato water.
Peel and dice 1 medium potato. Cook in 2 1/2 cups water until well done, about 20 minutes.
Pour potatoes and water through strainer or blend in blender until well blended.
It should look like milky, cloudy water, and is used in making the bread.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saut onion and carrots in the oil.
Add water and bouillon cubes and cook until cubes dissolve.
Add noodles, broccoli and salt.
Bring to a slow boil and add salt.
Just before serving, add milk and cheese until cheese melts.

title: wilma's swedish meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onions, salt, pepper, nutmeg and curry powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into small balls 1-inch in diameter.
Brown balls in melted shortening a few at a time.
Add more shortening if needed.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all but jello and apple.
Bring to a boil.
Add jello and keep hot until jello dissolves.
Add apple and pour into a mold or 8 x 8-inch square dish.
Let set.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute bacon in deep saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add leeks and onion; saute 5 more minutes.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes for 1 hour.
Mix in blender or mash until creamy.
Combine egg yolks and sour cream; add to soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: marshmallow sugarless icing
directions: Beat egg whites with corn syrup in double boiler over hot water until thick and fluffy.
Stir in marshmallows.
Remove from heat; beat until icing holds peaks.
Delicious on Chocolate Cake.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast the 1 tablespoon sugar in lukewarm liquid. Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Add shortening and sugar that has been thoroughly creamed and eggs beaten light.
Then add all the rest of the flour and salt.
Turn on board and knead lightly.
Place in greased bowl and let rise for 2 hours.
Roll out in oblong pieces, 1/4 inch thick.
Brush with melted butter, sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins (optional).
Roll up lengthwise, cut as desired and put in greased pans to rise again for 1 hour or until light.
Bake and ice with plain powdered sugar.

title: soup-er burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns.
Garnish with onion, tomatoes and lettuce.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Marinade:

Peel and crush the garlic and; and ginger, mince fine; finely slice the onion; snip the parsley and chop coarsely. Combine the garlic, ginger, onion, parsley, cumin, chili powder, tumeric, oregano, olive oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, sherry, and the crushed red chili pepper.
(The marinade can be frozen and reused once or twice.)

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Simmer margarine, celery and onions until transparent.
Add Cheez Whiz and melt.
Add rice, broccoli, water and mushroom soup. Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pepper and corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except vinegar thoroughly in pot. Stir in vinegar gradually.
Bring to boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place in hot jars.
Seal and water-process 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: picnic party loaf
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add ham, a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix until almost smooth.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for several hours.
This can be done 1 day ahead.

title: date and bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, dates, raisins and boiling water.
In another large bowl, mix sugar, oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add cereal mixture.
Put paper liners in muffin tins and fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients with egg mixture and blend thoroughly.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when depressed. After removing from oven, turn hot bread out of pan onto foil sprinkled with granulated sugar.
While hot, wrap closely in the foil.
When cool, store in the refrigerator until needed.

title: orange pecans
directions: Put sugar and orange juice in a large saucepan and cook to soft ball stage.
Turn off heat and add orange rind and pecans. Stir with wooden spoon until mixture turns cream color, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper on cookie sheet.
When cool enough to handle, break apart.
Serves 6.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in water.
Using beaters, add cream cheese.
Add drained pineapple, nuts and 1/2 cup of pineapple juice.
Cool until slightly set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: alaska oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Place the raisins and water in a saucepan and boil for 5 minutes, covered.
Remove from heat, but do not take off the lid until the raisins are cool.
Sift and measure flour.
Add baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sift again to mix; set aside.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour mixture and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins. Do not add extra liquid from raisins.
I dip them out with slotted spoon.
Spray cookie sheet.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 13 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Accent together. Dip pork chops in egg mixture and then in cracker crumbs. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown. Serve with bread stuffing with walnuts added. Also serve with scalloped potatoes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix together the chicken, celery, soup, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice, water chestnuts and noodles.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Spread on top the cornflakes, mixed with butter (melted).
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef parmigiana
directions: Place meat between pieces of waxed paper larger than the meat and lay on a board.
Pound meat thin (1/4 inch) with a heavy mallet.
Trim off gristle and fat; cut into 6 to 8 pieces.
Dip meat in egg, roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese and crumbs.
Heat oil in skillet, brown steaks on both sides over medium heat until golden brown.
Lay in shallow, wide baking dish.
In same skillet, cook onion over low heat until soft.
Stir in salt, pepper, sugar, marjoram and tomato paste, plus hot water, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes, scraping browned bits from pan.
Pour most of sauce over meat, top with slices of Mozzarella cheese and remaining sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add Bisquick; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour and cheeses. Add milk; cook and stir until mixture boils.
Stir in broccoli. Place in a 1-quart casserole and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: twix bars
directions: Boil 5 minutes the graham crackers, sugars, butter and milk, stirring often.
Place a layer of Club crackers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of boiled mixture on top of crackers.
Place another layer of crackers in pan and spread remaining mixture over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over top.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put cake mix in a deep bowl and add dry Jell-O; beat with mixer until blended.
Combine water and salad oil; add to cake mix and Jell-O.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Add half mashed strawberries; mix well.
Bake at 350° in three 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Cool before frosting.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and nuts. Stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and onion and let cook.
Stir in Ragu and tomato paste and add 1 or 2 cans water.
Sprinkle oregano over sauce and stir in.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Mix together cottage cheese, 2 beaten eggs, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, start layers with enough sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Noodles next, then cottage cheese mixture (spread very thin).
Then Mozzarella cheese.
Then sauce.
Repeat at least twice.
End with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes and uncovered for 30 minutes. Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: weight watchers chocolate cakeeverton, missouri
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in small pan sprayed with Pam at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: personal pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split English muffins.
Place on cookie sheet.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons of pizza sauce on each English muffin half.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with favorite topping.
I use 2 slices of pepperoni to each English muffin half.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts and edges are brown.

title: autumn soup
directions: Simmer until vegetables are done; take bay leaf out before serving.

title: thyme-buttered crescents
directions: Cream the butter until fluffy; stir in lemon juice and thyme. Keep herb butter at room temperature for 1 hour to mellow before using.

title: chocolate walnut chess tarts
directions: Melt margarine in large bowl.
Add cocoa and sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into purchased unbaked tart shells.
Bake at 350° degrees for about 20 minutes or just until cracks begin to form on top of filling.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, layer English peas, then crumble a layer of crackers.
Continue and pour soup over all and sprinkle cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: f~b~i chicken in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: fruit cake
directions: Will also need two buttered and floured 6-cup molds.

title: 7 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs. Combine flavor and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk (put flavoring in milk).
Spoon into greased Bundt pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine meat and marinade.
Marinate for 2 hours.

title: crock-pot cornish hens and vegetables
directions: Place potatoes, carrots and bell pepper in crock-pot.
Put hens on top.
Season.
Place butter on top.
Cook on low overnight.
Delicious.

title: caramelized onion rings
directions: Separate onion slices into rings, set aside.
In heavy nonstick frypan, evenly sprinkle sugar and heat over medium heat until sugar melts and starts to brown.
When sugar is medium brown, add butter, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
When butter starts to bubble, add the onion rings.
Raise the heat slightly and saute, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent and covered with dark brown caramel sauce, about 6 or 8 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: yellow coconut cake
directions: To make frosting:
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet; add 2 cups coconut.
Stir over low heat until brown and toasted.
In bowl, cream softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add milk, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups of the toasted coconut.
Frost cake.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup toasted coconut on sides and top.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix
cracker
crumbs and melted butter well.
In casserole or baking
dish,
place
a
layer of 1/2 of the buttered crumbs, 1/2 the grated cheese and a layer of asparagus spears. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Top with the remainder of grated cheese.
Cover with remainder of buttered cracker crumbs. Bake for 20 minutes in preheated oven at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: snowball cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add flour, salt and vanilla; beat until blended. Add nuts and mix by hand.

title: crustless asparagus quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute scallions until soft in 1 teaspoon margarine.
Combine scallions, asparagus, milk, eggs, 1 ounce cheese and seasonings.
Butter a 7-inch pie dish with remaining margarine; pour in egg mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: death by chocolate(serves 18 to 20)
directions: Bake cake as directions indicate; while still warm pierce with fork and pour on Kahlua or coffee.
Set aside.
Make pudding and chill.
Break cake in small pieces.
Crush the candy bars and shave the milk chocolate bar.
Layer in large glass bowl or trifle dish as follows:
cake, pudding, crushed candy, sprinkle with chocolate chips, sprinkle with nuts, Cool Whip.
Continue until bowl is full.
End with Cool Whip and top with shaved candy bar. Refrigerate a couple of hours.

title: batter fried cornish hen
directions: Thaw Rock Cornish hens and quarter.
Beat egg slightly and combine with milk.
Gradually add to flour, mixed with salt; stir to a smooth batter.

title: pistachio puffs
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and pudding together.
Slice Puffs in half and put the filling between.

title: corned beef-dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve in hollowed out bread round or spread on party bread slices.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Combine the 1/4 cup corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine.
In medium size saucepan, cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, stirring until well coated.
Press evenly in 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Stir together peanut butter fudge sauce and the 3 tablespoons corn syrup.
Spread half the peanut butter mixture over crust until firm.
Allow ice cream to soften slightly.
Spoon into frozen crust and spread evenly.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice the steak into very thin strips, about 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches In a large skillet heat the butter.
Saute the onions and garlic, stirring frequently.
Add the steak and mushrooms and cook until the meat is browned on all sides.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding one egg at a time.	Pour in two loaf pans.	Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast	in
cup warm water with 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Pour boiling water over oats, whole wheat, salt, cooking oil
and
honey
and
cool	to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast and enough bread flour to finish.
Knead twice and bake in a 400° oven
for
minutes,
then
at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese chip dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Beat until creamy.
Add milk and hot sauce to taste.
Mix well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix warm spaghetti with Salad Supreme seasoning and Italian dressing.
Add chopped vegetables and olives.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients (works well in processor).
Roll into 1-inch balls; roll in crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate intrigue cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; blend in eggs, one at a time.
Mix all with milk and vanilla.
Blend well.
Turn 2/3 of batter into 10-inch tube pan, greased on bottom.
Add syrup, soda and vanilla to remaining batter; mix well.
Pour over white batter and bake in 350° oven for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender and cool.
Pull off bone. Add back to broth and cook with potatoes, onions and carrots. When vegetables are cooked, add noodles and cook about 8 minutes longer.

title: holiday pecans
directions: Beat egg white with 1 tablespoon water; coat pecans with mixture.
Mix sugar with cinnamon and salt.
Coat pecans and stir. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, then stir.
Decrease temperature to 250° and bake additional 30 minutes.
Let cool, then enjoy.

title: chess pie(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar. Stir meal and flour into eggs; mix well. Stir in milk and butter; add vinegar and vanilla. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: jewish apples
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: hasty pudding
directions: Boil water, brown sugar and butter for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla; mix remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls in sauce. Bake 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dressing with chicken
directions: Boil chicken until very tender. It's very important that chicken is tender. Debone. Save broth.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dip roast in seasoned flour and brown well.
Simmer in pot with water to cover until tender.
Remove roast and cool.
Add to the pot of stock:
carrots, onion, potatoes, cabbage and celery. Add enough water to cover and boil until tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oil; add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Add water and dry ingredients and mix together.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple burras
directions: Place 1/2 cup of filling in center of each tortilla.
Dot with margarine.
Fold tortilla and place folded side down on a lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Place in freezer until almost solid.
Serve as slush.

title: orange crackling bread
directions: In 9-inch ovenproof skillet, cook salt pork over low heat until very crisp.
Remove and chop finely; drain off all but 1 tablespoon of fat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
In large bowl mix together corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In small bowl beat eggs with buttermilk and orange juice.
Add egg mixture all at once to dry ingredients and stir just until mixed.
Stir in salt pork and onion.
Heat the skillet.
Turn in batter and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot with butter.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Can use any kind of veggies you like.

title: *stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cored cabbage in a large pot of boiling water, removing leaves as they soften.
In 4 tablespoons oil saute chopped onion. When soft, remove to a large bowl.
To oil in pan, add additional 1/2 cup oil, crushed tomatoes and 1 Knorr cube.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cream freezer salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Oil a mold and fill with mixture.
Cover tightly and freeze 24
hours.
Set out 20 minutes before serving.
Unmold and serve.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Pear juice and water make 1 cup.
Heat and set Jell-O until it starts to thicken.
Beat cream cheese with milk.
Add Jell-O to pears.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: nutty chocolate chip pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a medium mixing bowl, beating at low speed.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour. Gradually stir in chocolate morsels, pecans and coconut.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour kraut
directions: Pack in quart fruit jars.
Put water to top, then add 1 teaspoon of salt and seal lid.

title: garlic spread
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Make incision around head of garlic to remove the outer skin from the top half of head.
Arrange in a baking dish which will hold them (about 7-inch).
Dot with butter. Pour 1/3 cup olive oil over heads.
Salt and pepper well.
Put thyme here and there.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes; then uncovered, basting every 15 minutes.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer. Serve by spreading garlic and soft white cheese on Italian bread.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup margarine.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs. Combine food coloring and cocoa, making a paste.
Add to mixture. Add alternately to mixture the buttermilk, flour and vanilla. Mix quickly in jar or cup of vinegar and soda.
Then add to batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: beef & cheese fold over
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce and set aside.
Heat oven to 375° F.
Unroll crescent dough into 4 long rectangles on ungreased cookie sheet, overlapping long sides. Firmly press perforations and edges to seal.
Pat to form 15 x 13 in. rectangle.
Spread meat mixture lengthwise in a 4 in. strip down center of dough to within 1 in. of end.
Top meat with cheese slices, fold shorter sides of dough 1 in. over filling.
Bring long sides of dough rectangle over filling overlapping edges. Pinch to seal.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 375° F for 20 - 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening and peanut butter and mix well.
Gradually add granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Cream thoroughly after each addition.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Add sifted flour and mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet or roll dough into balls 3/4 to 1-inch in diameter.
Press lightly with a fork to flatten.
Bake at 325° (slow oven) 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine other ingredients except cracker crumbs; sprinkle them on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water; stir into hot cheese mixture.
Cool, then add whipping cream and nuts.
Pour into dish and chill until firm.
May use Cool Whip in place of cream.

title: raisin brown bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake approximately 50 minutes or until bread pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: coffee crumb cake
directions: Mix butter, 1/4 cup
sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, sour milk and vanilla.

title: pineapple syrup
directions: Heat together pineapple juice and apple juice.
Mix together cornstarch and water.
Add to hot juice and heat until thickened. Add crushed pineapple.
Stir.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then knead; put into greased bowl and let raise 2 hours.
Roll out dough and cut into roll shape; bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix butter and honey in small bowl until blended.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: brides punch
directions: Combine juices, ginger ale and water.
Just before serving, put in the sherbet.
You can use orange and pineapple sherbet. This is good!

title: cheese cubes
directions: Blend cheese spread and butter until softened and well blended. Put bread in refrigerator to make it firm.
Trim the crust and cut approximately 1-inch squares.
Spread on all sides with cheese mixture.
Grease cookie sheet.
Brown cubes in a 375° to 400° oven for 5 minutes or until brown.
Serve hot.
Can be prepared ahead of time and frozen (unbaked).
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and let stand overnight.

title: pioneer apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Bake 1 pie crust at 350° until golden brown.
Heat apples with water (undrained), 1 cup apple juice and rum extract to a gentle simmer until apples are soft.
In small bowl combine 1/2 cup apple juice, cornstarch, apple pie spices and salt.
Mix well.
Add slowly to simmering apples.
Stir gently but completely.
Cook for 1 minute after mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir 1 cup Equal into mixture.
Cool and pour into cooled pie shell. Place uncooked pie shell on top of filled shell. Seal and crimp around edges.
Brush with water.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: sour cream potato salad
