directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: mexican delight
directions: Saute the onion in oil.
Add beef; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through; simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over spaghetti, noodles or rice.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Then add other ingredients and mix well until creamy.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: coconut shrimp
directions: Whisk together the flour and wine or beer until batter is smooth.
Dip shrimp in batter, then dip into the shredded coconut, turning to coat all sides.
Pour oil into large, deep frying pan; heat over high heat to 375°.
To be sure oil is hot enough, drop shred of coconut into oil; it should begin sizzling immediately.
Fry shrimp in 2 to 3 batches without crowding, turning occasionally, until cooked through and curled and coconut is golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove shrimp with a slotted spoon; drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings (3 shrimp each).

title: almond float
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup water; let stand 1 minute.
In a large saucepan, bring the remaining 2 cups water to a boil.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add evaporated milk and almond extract.
Stir in dissolved gelatin. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate until set.
When set, cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place almond gelatin in a bowl and add fruit; toss gently.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lye soap
directions: Melt grease and cool it.
Slowly pour lye in melted grease and stir.
Be careful while stirring.
Let mixture set completely.

title: microwave marmalade carrots
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes in the microwave on Medium-high.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan; cook for 10 minutes.
Watch to prevent boiling over.
Skim off the white froth.
Cool.
Serves 6.

title: salsa
directions: Cook together until desired taste and thickness.
Can, as you would other foods.
If too hot for taste, add tomato sauce only when ready to eat.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat flour and sugar into eggs.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate bits and walnuts.
Pour into a pie shell; bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: deluxe macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: b l m k h hush puppies
directions: Mix together with just enough milk that mixture will slide off spoon easily, drop in hot oil, brown until inside is cooked well.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Melt margarine and add to eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cover with miniature marshmallows when you take from oven.
Make icing while cake is baking and pour over marshmallows.

title: reese's cups
directions: Cream magarine and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Make small patties 1/2-inch thick.
Melt over hot water the chocolate chips and 1/4 block of paraffin wax.
Line muffin pans with cupcake papers.
Cover bottom with 1 tablespoon chocolate mixture.
Add peanut butter patties.
Cover with chocolate.
Cool. May use almond bark instead of paraffin mixture.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness and plenty of faith.
Mix well with love, patience, understanding and a dash of laughter. Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everybody you meet.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream sugars, margarine and eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad(12 servings)
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Chop onion fine.
Fry bacon crisp and set aside.
Add raisins.
Mix dressing and pour over the vegetables.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and Tang in bowl.
Pour juice from pineapple into mixture.
Add fruit (drained), pineapple and 2 bananas.

title: lettuce and pea salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish and spread Miracle Whip on top.
Then sprinkle the bacon on top of this, followed with the Parmesan cheese.
Chill overnight.

title: "no excuse" bread
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Soften yeast in a little warm water.
Add honey, sugar or molasses and set aside about 15 minutes (while you eat breakfast or wash dishes).
Mix flour and salt; gradually stir in yeast mixture.
Add water or milk until dough is consistency of thick porridge (more moist than the usual bread dough).
Spoon dough into 3 greased loaf pans. Set in warm place until dough rises nearly to the top of pans. (This will allow another 20 to 30 minutes to do odds and ends about the house.)
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375° until crusty. Turn out on rack to cool.

title: abelskivers
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add milk, then dry ingredients. Fold in beaten egg whites. Using an abelskiver pan, fill each hole 1/2- full of oil or crisco. Heat; fill wells with batter. Right away begin turning them, one at a time, until all are turned and cooked. They are small and round, and are done fast. Makes 4 dozen.

title: patricia's chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add almonds, mayo and soup.
Mix and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Take out and sprinkle Chinese noodles on top.
Return to oven for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: church eggs
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch squares and cover bottom of 6 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix ingredients (minus bread) and pour over bread squares.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until center is dry.

title: pom pom's pound cake
directions: Beat butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and milk, a little of each at a time.
Add lemon and almond.
Put in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: blue cheese crisps
directions: Combine butter and Blue cheese in a small bowl.
Blend well. Stir in pecans or walnuts.
Cut rolls in 1/3-inch slices.
Toast desired number of slices on one side.
Spread Blue cheese mixture on untoasted sides.
Broil until bubbling.
Store remaining spread in an airtight refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups spread, enough for about 48 appetizers.

title: coca-cola ham
directions: Place ham on heavy aluminum foil.
Cover ham with pineapple rings and add a cherry to each ring.
Pack brown sugar in holes of pineapple before adding the cherries and around the pineapple rings.
Fold up the aluminum foil, leaving an opening on top. Pour Coca-Cola through the opening and over ham.
Close the opening.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over mixed salad vegetables.

title: taco filling
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes; break up with a spoon.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer gently for 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken delight
directions: Remove skin from chicken, wash chicken and place in baking dish.
Season each chicken breast with a small amount of salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup and chicken soup over chicken and spread.
Add enough water to cover chicken.
Bake at 350° or 400° until chicken breasts are done.
Remove from oven and top chicken with biscuits.
Return to oven and bake at temperature specified on can until biscuits are golden brown.

title: linguine with chicken and asparagus
directions: Remove	all
sinews
and
soft	cartilage
from chicken breast.
Cut
the
breast into small strips about 1 1/2 inches long and 1/2
inch	wide.
There
should
be about 1 1/2 cups. Scrape and	trim the asparagus.
Cut off and discard any tough ends.
Cut	the
asparagus	on
the
diagonal
into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Drop
the
pieces into boiling, salted water; drain. Set aside.
Bring
enough
water
to a boil to cook the pasta; add pasta and cook to the desired degree of doneness.

title: baklava
directions: Butter base and sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and place 9 sheets of fillo separately into dish, brushing each with butter. Mix nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and spices and spread half of this mixture over fillo.
Top with 2 sheets of fillo, brushing each with butter. Spread remaining nuts on top and finish with remaining fillo, brushing each with butter.

title: sweet potato pineapple casserole
directions: Beat all together.
Butter baking dish.
Place 1/2 of mixture in dish.
Dot with marshmallows, then add remaining mixture.

title: pork loin in puff pastry
directions: Roll out defrosted puff pastry to 13 x 16-inch.
Salt and pepper fillet and brown in oil.
Saute shallots in butter.
Add diced mushrooms.
Saute until all liquid is gone, then add mustard.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop your green onions and same blades too.
Chop radishes and chipped beef.
Mix all ingredients together and then roll into ball and then roll in chopped pecans.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Thoroughly blend flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Make a well in center, add pumpkin, eggs, oil, water and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts and fold in well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in shortening with fork until crumbly.
Stir in milk.
Mix enough to wet the dry ingredients.
Drop dough from tablespoon onto a greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes about 4 biscuits.

title: mother's old time molasses cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly. Blend in well beaten egg and molasses.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 5 to 6 baby loaf tins.

title: betty knick's pot roast
directions: Cook on top of stove.
Salt, pepper and flour meat; brown in pot using oil.
Remove meat from pot; drain excess grease.
Mix soup, water, tomato sauce and soup mix; bring to a boil and add roast.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add onions.
Simmer for 1/2 hour. Add carrot chunks.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add potatoes.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: apple harvest
directions: Cut butter into flour, sugar and salt until crumbly.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange apples on top and sprinkle lemon juice on top.
Combine sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar with remaining ingredients and spoon over.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel carrots; slice and cook in small amount of water until barely tender.
Drain and cool.
Place a layer of carrots in a shallow dish.
Top with layer of green pepper and layer of onion. Repeat until all is used.

title: hawaiian cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together; chill well.
Serve with crackers, vegetables or fruit.

title: spicy ginger-garlic chicken
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine garlic, ginger root, salt, red pepper, black pepper, cinnamon and cardamom.
Stir in ketchup, vinegar and water.
Set aside.
Rinse chicken breasts; pat dry with paper towels.
Brush both sides of each chicken breast with garlic mixture.
Place chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until no longer pink.
Makes 8 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Set yeast and 1/2 cup warm water in small bowl to mix.
When yeast mixture is dissolved, in large bowl, put 1 cup warm water. Add flour and stir well.
Add eggs, sugar, shortening and salt. Stir well.
Set in refrigerator to cool or overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat
and
onion;
add beans, salt and seasoning. Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Gently
toss together with meat mixture.
Add crushed chips just before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add chicken, onion, pepper, pimento, celery, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, 1 can cream of chicken or cream of celery soup, 1 to 2 cups chicken broth and 1/2 stick oleo.
Mix together and bake at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Top with melted margarine mixed with Ritz cracker crumbs. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham barbecues
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes. Add ham and heat 5 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash beans; soak all day, then parboil about 1 hour.
Put in crock-pot, then add other ingredients.
Cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: cardinal chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Add chicken, celery, grapes, salad dressing and seasoning; mix lightly.
Press mixture into a 1 1/2-quart bowl; chill several hours.
Unmold on serving platter spread with lettuce leaves or choose the following option.

title: corn casserole
directions: Heat creamed corn, cream cheese and flour until cheese is melted.
Add onion, mushrooms and whole corn.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.

title: christmas rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour in oven.
Stir approximately 3 times while cooking.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
Cool and slice into 2 more layers. Use a piece of sewing thread to slice.
Mix sugar and sour cream. Add 1 1/2 packages of the coconut.
Place filling between layers and sprinkle with remainder of coconut.
Let stand several hours before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Freezes well and stays moist a long time.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cut sausage into tiny pieces.
Fry until done.
Drain.
Pinch bread into small pieces in a large container.
Add sausage, pickles, onions, celery, black pepper and broth.
Add broth slowly and just enough to make the mixture stick together. Put into a baking dish or casserole dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° until heated through. Brown top of dressing.

title: chicken cheese enchiladas(ultra low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut chicken in long strips and brown in skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
When chicken is brown, add onion and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a bowl, combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Very gradually add chicken broth to sour cream mixture, stirring constantly.
Don't add broth too fast.
When thoroughly mixed, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to boil. Add shredded cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Dip tortilla in the enchilada sauce, making sure both sides are covered with sauce.
Fill with chicken-onion mixture and cheese.
Roll tortilla, when filled, and place in a small casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.
When all filled and rolled, pour cheese and sour cream mixture over rolled tortillas.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: last minute dessert
directions: Beat egg.
Add rest of ingredients except fruit.
Mix on low until blended.
Spread in 9-inch pan.
Place fruit evenly on top of batter.
Batter will rise in between fruit to cover it.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Whip softened cream cheese.
Add sugar and sour cream.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into a loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: new peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large saucepan over low heat, stir together first three ingredients.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press into pan.
Cool.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Makes 32.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift 2 cups flour and salt, cut in shortening.
Add egg yolk and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir with fork.
Form into a ball.
Pat half of the dough into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place apples on dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and remaining flour and cinnamon. Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Roll other half of dough out thin. Cover with the apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with mixture of powdered sugar and remaining butter and milk.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Saute onion until soft in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer all for 10 minutes on low heat.
Divide short ribs or spareribs for serving.
Place in shallow pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Brush every 1/2 hour with the sauce and turn. Serves 4 to 6.

title: electric chicken
directions: Flour chicken and brown in oil at 250°.
Drain chicken and pour off oil.
In a bowl, mix small amount of water with 2 tablespoons of flour, then add rest of ingredients; mix well. Return chicken to skillet and pour liquid mixture over chicken. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles and green vegetable.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and butter; add flour, salt and cayenne.
Mix, roll and chill.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, 1 stick melted butter, eggs and vanilla in a 2-quart greased baking dish.
In a separate bowl, combine 1/3 cup melted butter, brown sugar and flour.
Spread flour mixture over sweet potatoes.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate biscotti
directions: Adjust oven racks to divide oven into thirds.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread almonds in single layer in shallow baking dish and bake on lower oven rack until lightly browned and crisp, 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool completely; coarsely chop and set aside.
Lower oven temperature to 300°.
Line baking sheet with parchment paper. In small bowl with wire whisk, combine flour, cocoa, coffee powder (if using), baking soda and salt.
In food processor, combine chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup flour mixture.
Process until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in remaining flour mixture and set aside.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Saute mushrooms and onion in bacon drippings; drain.
Mix bacon, mushrooms and onion with beans in a 2-quart baking dish.
Microwave cheese spread and pour over bean mixture.

title: aunt cordella's mince pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and spices in a bowl.
Add apple, raisins, cranberry sauce, nuts, orange and lemon peel and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust, tucking edges under rim of bottom crust; crimp edges.
With knife, cut design in top crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat. Stir small amount hot mixture into slightly beaten eggs, immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add 4 tablespoons of margarine and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Line sides and bottom of large dish with graham crackers and slice 3 to 4 bananas on this before adding the filling.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in quarters.
Remove cores; slice thin.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Mix sugar, flour and spices; rub a little mixture into pastry.
Arrange sliced apples, overlapping in pan.
Add remaining sugar mixture.
Dot with butter or margarine.

title: cheese ball
directions: Keep Swiss cheese, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese at room temperature. Beat cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy.
Add Swiss cheese and Cheddar cheese and beat.
Add other ingredients (bacon, onion, pimiento, relish, salt, pepper and parsley).
Chop pecans. Shape cheese mixture into a ball.
Cover ball with pecans.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and walnuts.
Add milk, 1 tablespoon at a time, until mixture is creamy and easily stirred.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes until brown around edges.
Remove to wire racks and cool.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: pasta italiano bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Cover. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly by hand.
Pinch off small balls and shape. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
(Balls should be lightly browned.) Let cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Makes 48.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Drain,
cut
up and chop up peaches.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and
butter,
add
eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Mix
dry ingredients together and add to the mixture. Fold
in
the
sour
cream and peaches.
Pour into a Bundt pan or tube
pan.
I
spray my Bundt pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes.
Check to see if done by placing toothpick in cake. When it comes out clean, it's done.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Pour into a lightly sprayed tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with a thin powdered sugar icing.

title: vegetable dip #2
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add onions, bell pepper, pimentos, garlic and hot sauce; blend all together.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or meat.

title: essie's barbecue ribs
directions: Bake ribs for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven (no seasoning).
Pour grease off of ribs.
Mix sauces together; pour over ribs and bake 1 hour.

title: grandma's southern fried tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes but do not peel.
Cut into slices 1/2 to 3/4-inch.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine dry ingredients.
Dust slices of tomatoes in flour mixture on both sides.
Add milk to remaining flour mixture to make a thick batter.
Dip tomato slices in batter.
Fry in hot oil 1/2-inch deep until golden brown on both sides.
Drain before serving and serve hot.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot water to soften (or microwave for 30 seconds on High).
Warm chili.
Put generous tablespoon of chili toward edge of tortilla.
Sprinkle onions and cheese on top of chili.
Roll tortilla.
Pin roll with toothpick and lay in greased pan.
Continue until all tortillas are filled with chili, onions and cheese. Spread the rest of the chili, onions and cheese over rolled-up tortillas.
Use more chili, if desired. For extra zip, add 2 tablespoons canned green chilies. Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Can be served with sour cream over the top.
Serves 4.

title: spoon rolls(no kneading, no rising)
directions: Mix together the dry yeast, sugar, lukewarm water and beaten egg.
Add melted shortening and flour.
Store in refrigerator. Keeps one week.
Use as much or as little dough as you need at each time.
Drop by teaspoons into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: microwave turkey au gratin
directions: In a 2-quart micro-safe casserole, combine celery, onion and butter.
Micro-cook, covered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add milk.
Micro-cook, covered, on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until steaming and foamy, but not boiling.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Let stand, covered, 2 minutes.
Stir in turkey, soup, stuffing mix, 1/2 cheese and if desired, chili peppers. Micro-cook, covered, on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Let stand until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In spaghetti pot put 1-1/2 qt. (6 cups) boiling water,
dry onion soup and spaghetti.
Cook until spaghetti is tender.
Do not drain liquid.
Add browned meat and a jar of your favorite spaghetti sauce.
In 9x13 pan, layer as follows:
1/2 spaghetti mixture and 2 c. shredded mozzarella cheese.
Add the remaining spaghetti mixture and 2 c. cheese. Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: frozen raspberry macadamia dessert
directions: Mix nuts, vanilla wafers and margarine together to form crust. Press into 8-inch spring-form pan and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Heat butter in saucepan until melted; cook and stir garlic in butter until light brown.
Stir in 2 tablespoons parsley and clams.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over hot spaghetti.

title: commerce union tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in gallon container and fill with water. Add fresh mint for extra flavor.
Serve chilled.

title: macaroni kielbasa casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix with soup, broccoli and kielbasa and shredded Cheddar.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sesame pecan chicken
directions: Combine garlic, 1 teaspoon salt and buttermilk.
Let chicken marinate in mixture for at least 2 hours (can marinate overnight).

title: seven ribbon salad
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
In another pan, add 1/2 cup cold water to the unflavored gelatine.
Add to hot milk mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Cool.
Add the sour cream to this mixture.
Dissolve the jello, one box at a time, with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour one flavor into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Once the first layer of jello is set, pour 1 1/2 cups of sour cream mixture over jello.
Refrigerate until set.
Repeat this procedure with each package of jello.
Kids love this!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch round balls. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chips special
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, sugars and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate morsels, nuts and pecan meal.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 120 (2-inch) cookies.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg. In a second bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda to 1 cup persimmon pulp in 3rd bowl.
Combine all ingredients in 3 bowls.
Add walnuts, dates and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix canned soups, water and rice.
Put chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
Remember, don't peek!

title: thursday lunch club soup
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add ingredients.
Let simmer all day. (Add macaroni prior to serving if you choose to use it.)

title: veal and smithfield ham swirls
directions: Saute green onions in 1/2 cup butter in a large skillet until tender.
Remove from heat; add next 5 ingredients.
Stir well and set aside.
Flatten veal steaks to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Spread mustard evenly over veal; top each steak with a ham slice.

Pat 1/4 cup onion mixture evenly over ham slices; roll up jellyroll fashion and secure with a wooden pick. Place veal rolls, seam side down, on a rack in a shallow pan. Brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Remove veal from pan to serving platter. Remove toothpicks and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: myrtle beach thousand island
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend.
Refrigerate.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: You will need 1 large bowl and a mixer.

title: soyamel topping
directions: Mix water and Soyamel powder in blender.
Add sugar, if used, and vanilla and blend.
While blender is still on full speed, pour in oil very slowly, in a thin stream, until you reach the consistency of whipped cream.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger in frying pan with onion and fresh carrots until done.
Drain grease.
Return mixture to pan and add beef bouillon, tomato paste and flour; simmer on medium heat.

title: blackberry syrup
directions: Bring all to hard boil for 2 minutes.
Skim off any foam. Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: barbecue
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper, mustard, lemon juice, onion and oleo.
Simmer uncovered on low for about 15 minutes.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce and drained meat. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
If barbecue seems too dry because of the lean meat, add some water and a little more catsup.

title: bordelaise sauce(servings:  4)
directions: Cook shallots in red wine until reduced to 1/4 the original quantity.
Add 1 cup of bordelaise sauce and mix gently for 10 minutes.
Have ready a beef marrow bone which the butcher has split so that the marrow can be removed easily.
Cut the marrow in small dices; poach it in boiling salted water for 1 or 2 minutes and drain.
Just before serving, add 2 tablespoons of this beef marrow and 1/2 teaspoon chopped parsley.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place cubed bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread cooked sausage over bread, then top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread, sausage and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until eggs are done.
Excellent for Thanksgiving or Christmas morning.

title: pineapple cheeseball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 1 cup pecans inside ball and 1 cup pecans to roll ball in.
Refrigerate approximately 4 hours. Serve with assorted crackers and breads.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Drain and let stand 5 minutes before serving. Bake at 350°.

title: turkey leftover stir-fry
directions: Combine broth, soy sauce, vinegar, cornstarch and crushed red pepper.
In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add pepper strips and scallions.
Cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Stir in ginger and garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in chicken broth mixture. Reduce heat to medium.
Add turkey.
Bring to a simmer.
Cook until slightly thickened, about 3 minutes.
Serve over rice with peanuts and cilantro.

title: crisp little lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in the large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls, pressing firmly.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 9 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown around the edges.
Remove from baking sheets.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Grease and flour loaf pans. Recipe will make 2 large loaves or 4 medium loaves.
Medium loaves should be baked in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Larger loaves for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs gently with sugar.
Add oil, water and pumpkin. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to mixture.
Add nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaf pans.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Core and chop apples.
Cut grapes in half.
Remove seeds (if any).
In bowl, mix ingredients by following recipe.
Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, biscuit mix and cheese with hand.
Shape loosely into marble-sized balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields approximately 100 balls.

title: cold tomato relish
directions: Let tomatoes
drain
overnight with the 1/2 cup of salt in a colander.
Stir
in
all the other ingredients.
Seal in jars and process.

title: congealed rice salad *
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar, water and rice; let jell.
Whip pineapple, pecans and whipped cream.
Add to other mixture.
Pour into dish and let set a while in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook a young turkey breast 6 hours in a crock-pot; separate in pieces.
Add stuffing to broth.
Mix in turkey.
Top with turkey gravy mix.
Cook 1/2 to 1 hour in the crock-pot.

title: cajun potato wedges
directions: Place potato wedges on lined cookie tray.
Melt margarine and mix garlic salt together.
With brush, cover every wedge. Sprinkle Cajun seasoning on wedges.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put ground beef in frying pan.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Brown. Drain grease; then add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Simmer about 3 hours.
Remove bay leaves and serve over hot spaghetti.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: creamed onions
directions: Boil onions in salted water until tender, but firm.
Drain.

title: dill pickles
directions: Prepare
home
canning jars and lids according to manufacturer's instructions.
Wash cucumbers, trim ends.
Cut into halves
or
quarters,
lengthwise.
Combine water, vinegar and salt,
bring to a boil.
Pack cucumbers into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Add 2
heads
of dill or 2 teaspoons dill seed, 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed and 2 peppercorns to each jar. Carefully pour hot
liquid
over
cucumbers,
leaving 1/4 inch headspace. Remove air
bubbles
with
a non-metallic spatula. Adjust caps. Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath canner. Makes about 7 pint jars.

title: round steak with gravy
directions: Cut into several pieces.
Flour both sides and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon flour mixture in water and pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake for 4 hours at 250°.
This is very tender.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 350° and bake until golden brown.

title: italian dumplings
directions: Mix enough flour to make dough hard enough to roll.
Shape into rolls; cut thin.
Mash them down more; drop into boiling soup.
If soup stops boiling, wait until the soup boils again; otherwise, your dumplings will stick together and be soggy.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix angel food cake mix according to package directions.
Add coconut and lemon pie filling and spread in greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
DO NOT OVERBAKE. Top with Cream Cheese Frosting if desired.
(Is good without the frosting.)

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and oleo.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour, coconut and nuts.
Bake in sheet pan for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
When cake is done and still hot, spread a large jar of marshmallow cream over the top.
Let cool and then frost with the following:

title: chicken flamenco
directions: Season the chicken with salt and pepper; brown in a nonstick skillet in margarine.
Transfer to a 3-quart or larger casserole. Add the diced pepper, celery and onions to the skillet; cook, stirring, for 5 minutes or until tender crisp.
Spoon the mixture over the chicken.
In a saucepan, bring broth to a boil; pour over the chicken and vegetables.
Cover the casserole and bake in a preheated 325° oven 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done. Add the mushrooms and pimento to casserole.
Return casserole to oven to finish baking chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: * three bean salad *
directions: Drain liquid from all the beans and place in a bowl.
Mix in green pepper and onion.
Combine sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil.
Pour over bean mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Letting this salad marinate at least a day or two improves the flavor.

title: hot beefs
directions: Place beef in large roaster.
Cover with water and beer. Roast at 350° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Drain off liquid and season with onion salt, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Grind beef cubes and mix back in seasoned liquid.
Mix well.
Freezes well.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat together.
About half way through browning, add onion and bell pepper.
Drain grease from meat mixture.
Pour mixture into large stockpot.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Simmer for at least an hour.
Serve with shredded cheese, sour cream and oyster crackers.
Yields approx. 15-20 bowls.
Freezes well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and bananas, mixing well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into banana mixture, just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours or until bread tests done.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs and beat well.
Add berries and fold in nuts.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Spread pineapple in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spoon pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle with dry cake mix and pecans.
Combine melted margarine and reserved juice in bowl; mix well.
Drizzle over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar together.
Melt peanut butter and 1 1/2 sticks butter together.
Mix graham cracker and sugar mixture with peanut butter mixture.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with mixture of chocolate chips and 1/2 stick butter.
Let cool at room temperature; cut in bars.
(May take more chips and butter.)

title: spaghetti cheese casserole
directions: Simmer ground chuck in skillet. Add a cup of water, salt and pepper. Grate fine the carrots, onions and peppers. Add to meat while simmering. Add mushrooms (juice and all). The last 40 minutes, add chili powder. Boil spaghetti. Add Velveeta while spaghetti is warm. Mix with meat and cover. Let stand 24 hours. Heat at 350° until warm. Serves 12.

title: prize biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together like pie crust.
Add milk and mix together.
Do not overmix.
Roll out, if desired, but are very light otherwise.
Add a little more sugar and use as short cakes, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in deviled ham.

Add garlic powder and enough mayonnaise to make it smooth. May add 1 ounce chopped pimiento, 1/2 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce, 2 tablespoons grated onion, 2 tablespoons pickle juice or catsup for variety.
A favorite with the men folk!

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Sift powdered sugar and cocoa.
Set aside.
Melt together margarine and Velveeta cheese in the microwave on Medium.
Pour melted mixture into sugar.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Spread into two slightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans. Cool and cut.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Prepare Bisquick mix as instructed by Bisquick directions for biscuits.
Roll out Bisquick on floured board or aluminum foil into a circle, as thin as possible, but still able to handle.
Should make approximately 12 to 15-inch circle.
Take sausage and pinch off small bite size portions and sprinkle over the circle of Bisquick dough; the thicker, the better it will be.
Roll Bisquick mix dough with sausage over it into jelly roll; may put oil or flour on hands for easy handling of jelly roll.
Pinch ends together and edge of dough to seal.
Roll up in wax paper and freeze until firm to make slicing easier.
Slice approximately 1/4-inch and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 400° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mozzarella chicken breast
directions: You also need 2 bowls with flat bottoms (Tupperware is great), large enough to hold 1 chicken breast.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Put eggs, seasonings, vinegar and 1/2 cup oil in blender container.
Cover and process at whip.
Immediately remove feeder cap and pour in the remaining oil in a steady thin stream.
Use rubber spatula, if necessary, to keep ingredients flowing into processing blades.

title: g. p. sandwiches
directions: Cut ham and cheese into small pieces.
Mix together.
Add relish, mustard and mayo.
You may need to add more mayo until moist.
Place mixture on buns.
Wrap individually in aluminum foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: Stir together potatoes, 1/2 cup melted butter, onion, salt, pepper, soup, cheese and sour cream.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with flakes. Drizzle with 1/2 cup melted butter. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: the james gang's cream cheese toast
directions: Spread 2 slices of bread generously with cream cheese and preserves.
Top with remaining bread.
Beat egg and milk together. Heat butter in large skillet.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture, coating on both sides.
Saute in butter until golden brown on both sides.
Serves 2.

title: crock-pot stew beef
directions: Melt 1 to 1 1/2 cups bacon grease. Roll birds in flour and brown evenly in bacon grease. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Remove and put in large casserole dish with thin gravy made from pan drippings. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve with rice.

title: chicken marsala(serves 4)
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter and saute onions 1 minute. Add mushrooms and saute until onions are soft. Remove from pan and set aside. Saute chicken breasts until no longer pink. Make roux with 1 tablespoon butter, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon paprika in separate pan. Stir wine into roux. Heat to high and add chicken stock, lemon juice, soy sauce and pepper. Reduce sauce to 1 cup (about 15 minutes). Add mushrooms, onions, chicken, 1 teaspoon chervil or parsley and a pinch of fines herbes. Lower heat and cook 5 minutes. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Form into balls, 2 teaspoons each.
Place on waxed paper or baking sheet and freeze. Melt chocolate chips and Crisco; blend.
With toothpicks dip balls into chocolate so 3/4 is coated.
Return to waxed paper.
Remove pick and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cuisinart pie crust
directions: Put butter, flour and salt in bowl with steel blade until it looks like grits.
Add water and cut off when ball forms.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Mix 2 cups powdered sugar and 2 to 3 teaspoons water, just enough to make a frosting that can be used easily in a decorator's tube and yet holds its shape.

title: chip bars
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spread dough on greased cookie sheet. Then put chocolate and/or buttered chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate-mayo cake
directions: Beat together the sugar, mayonnaise, cocoa and soda.
Add hot water.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add the flour and beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in large saucepan, add soups, sauce and chilies.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Grease a casserole dish, pour half of the mixture into dish, top with half of the cheese, place a layer of tortillas on top of cheese.
Add remaining mixture, again top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and press in ring mold. Place in refrigerator and chill.
Turn out and place preserves into center of ring.
Serve with crackers.

title: mom's secret b.b.q.  sauce
directions: Mix well and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Use on all grilled meats.
Dilute with a small amount of water if it gets too thick.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onions in margarine. Brown hamburger meat and pour in baking dish. Mix other ingredients, pour mushroom soup on top. Sprinkle another cup of cheese on top of this. Cook on low until done; about 25 minutes.

title: mountain momma mud slide cake
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, combine softened butter, flour and chopped nuts.
Mix well and press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup peppers; cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and 1/4 pound process cheese spread; continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Dip tortillas in hot oil; drain.
Fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup meat mixture; rollup.
Place, seam side down, in 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture; cover. Bake at 350°, 20 minutes.
Top with remaining process cheese spread; continue baking uncovered 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining peppers and tomatoes.

title: tuna and rice dinner
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet on medium heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender, but not browned.
Stir in vegetables, milk, soup and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in tuna, rice and parsley.
Cover.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.

title: spandango
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground chuck until done.
Drain. Add salt and pepper to taste and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Meanwhile, cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves eight.

title: simply sauteed cinnamon apples
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cherries and sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Place in sieve and let drain very well.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate and set aside.

title: can't catch me gingerbread men
directions: Add to above mixture and chill dough.
Roll to 1/8 inch thick. Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: dad's favorite homemade chili
directions: Brown meat with onions and bell pepper.
Add salt and pepper, chili powder, parsley flakes and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except red beans.
Let simmer for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add red beans last.

title: peanut-butterscotch squares
directions: In a bowl, melt butterscotch chips in the microwave at 30% until melted (about 3 1/2 minutes).
Add peanut butter and microwave at 30% for about 3 minutes more.
Add to Rice Krispies and spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm. Makes 16 to 20 bars.

title: pizza tray
directions: Spread very soft cream cheese in a 12-inch glass lipped dish or tray.
Pour on pizza sauce.
Layer olives, onion, pepper and mushrooms over sauce.
Sprinkle on cheese very generously.
(May be made the day before and refrigerated, but bring to room temperature before serving.)
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, and butter in glass saucepan.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and peanut butter until dissolved.
Stir in oats.
Drop from tablespoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: lime cheesecake
directions: Blend crust ingredients thoroughly.
Press crust over bottom and halfway up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: eggplant and beef casserole
directions: Cut onion in small pieces and saute in butter.
Add beef; cook until brown.
Combine tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper and pour over meat mixture.
Remove from heat.
Slice eggplant and brown lightly.
Place layer of eggplant in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add layer of meat mixture.
Repeat layer.
Pour sauce over all. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: liver with mushrooms
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients until browned.
Then add salt, oregano and wine.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In 1 tablespoon butter, saute mushrooms and onions until limp.
Remove to plate.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Add liver and saute until browned, about 2 minutes on each side.
Add salt, oregano and wine.
Heat to boil. Reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms and onions; heat briefly.

title: taco soup
directions: Serve with Fritos, taco chips and cheese.

title: glorified meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pack firmly in dish.
Save some tomato to spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut up cooked chicken.
Mix soups, sour cream and chicken. Add salt & pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and spread on top.
Melt butter and pour on crackers. Sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into inside chamber of a 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Finish filling up container to fill line with milk.
Stir with tumbler.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs, flour, margarine, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon or ham and cheese over top and gently press.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and reserve juice for later.
Brown ground beef; add onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Combine beef mixture and beans; add ketchup, barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Add chili powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste. Simmer together for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, mix together cherries and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and 1/3 cup sugar; beat in egg until blended.
Add flour mixture, orange rind and orange juice; stir only until flour mixture is moistened.
Spread over cherries.
Bake at 375° until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean of batter (about 45 minutes).
Makes 6 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour,	baking	powder,
baking
soda and salt. Sift this over
raisins	or
currants mixed with caraway seed. Stir well and add buttermilk to make a soft dough.

title: escalloped corn with jiffy corn muffin mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins in salted water until tender (about 25 minutes).
Drain, cool and peel.
Combine margarine, sugar and lemon juice in large skillet.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Add potatoes.
Heat slowly, spooning syrup over potatoes until glazed.
Stir in water; cover.
Heat 5 minutes longer.
Spoon into heated serving bowl; sprinkle rind on top. Makes 8 servings.

title: apples and apple dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and brown sugar.
Cut up apples and enjoy dip.

title: pineapple wet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Spread frosting.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add Italian spices and blend.
Stir in shrimp
by hand.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to allow spices to blend.
Serve with chips or vegies.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine with pastry cutter, flour, crisco and sugar. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients. Let rise 1 hour (can be baked without rising). Roll out & cut. Bake at 400 degrees for approximately 12 minutes.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining dry ingredients (in order listed) over melted butter. Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kelly's favorite butterscotch pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding until thick. Add Cool Whip. Beat and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: christmas salad
directions: Grind berries and orange rind.
Add sugar and let stand 2 hours.
Mix jello and hot water; when it starts to jell, add cranberry mixture and the rest of the ingredients.

title: toffee brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brownie mix, 3/4 cup Heath brickle, eggs and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: hard rolls
directions: Mix 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, margarine and yeast in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add warm water.
Beat at low speed, frequently scraping bowl, 1 minute.
Stir in enough flour, 1 cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased 2 1/2-quart bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and let rise, at room temperature until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough; cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 18 equal parts.
Shape into balls and roll in palm of the hand to make oblong shape and place on greased cookie sheets.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Mix egg whites and cold water; brush over rolls.
Make slash about 1 1/2-inches deep and 2 inches long on each roll.
Heat oven to 375° and place both cookie sheets in oven.
Bake 15 minutes.
Alternate cookie sheets; bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes more.
Makes 18 rolls.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Spread 2 cups bread crumbs in a baking dish.
Spread 2 cups applesauce (mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon to taste) over bread crumbs.
Heat in a warm oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce stack cake
directions: After mixing, take a handful of stiff dough and mash it into a round cake pan which has been lined with wax paper.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: holiday punch
directions: In the boiling water, steep the tea bags, cinnamon and cloves for 20 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices; add the sugar and stir until dissolved.
Dissolve the jello in another 2 cups of boiling water.
Add to the tea mixture.
Add the pineapple juice and the lemonade.
Divide the concentrate equally into 2 one-gallon containers (approximately 6 3/4 cups concentrate per container).
Add 7 cups water to each container.
Serve hot or cold over crushed ice.
Serves 50.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put into greased casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
An 8 ounce package of noodles makes a little over 4 cups, but may use whole package.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter in a huge pot. After melted, pour in Crispix cereal.
After cereal is mixed in, pour into a grocery sack with the powdered sugar, then shake. Ready to chow!

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl; serve.

title: carrot and pea casserole
directions: Scrub carrots and cook in boiling water (salted) for 5 minutes. Drain.
Chop parsley or celery leaves fine.
Cook along with chopped or minced onion in melted butter or margarine over low heat until onion is golden brown.
Stir flour into mixture until smooth. Add milk and stir until sauce is smooth and slightly thick.
Season with salt, pepper and chopped parsley.
Put cooked peas in medium-sized casserole.
Cover with carrots and pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes. In a large bowl, mix salt, boiling water, sugar and margarine. When cool add two eggs and yeast mixture, plus 6 cups plain flour. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Shape into rolls.
Cook at 375 degrees until brown.
Best when served warm.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick butter together. Set aside.
Cream sugar, eggs and 1 stick butter.
Add flour and soda.
Alternate with milk.
Add melted candy mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: quick barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place drummettes in 10-inch nonstick skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over drummettes.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken is done.

title: italiano dinner rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and next 5 ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Combine milk, water and 2 tablespoons margarine in a small bowl.
Stir until butter or margarine melts.
Cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Add milk mixture to flour mixture; beat at medium speed of electric mixer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add egg and beat until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix well and let set in refrigerator 24 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeps well in refrigerator until all is used.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it can be easily removed from bones.
Save broth (about 2 cups).
Put 1/2 of dressing mix in bottom of square pan and spoon broth over mix (about 1/2).
Put deboned chicken over mix.
In a small bowl, mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Pour the rest of the dressing mix over this and spoon remainder of broth over the top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Pour into baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix other ingredients.
I usually mix this and put in microwave to melt.
Stir it up good and pour over potatoes.
You may want to crumble corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together with an electric mixer until well blended.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 375 degrees for 1 hour.
Cool in dish and cut in squares.

title: cole slaw - homemade mayonnaise
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and 2 eggs.
Mix together.
Stir constantly with a wooden spoon or it will be lumpy.
Cook over medium heat.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into buttered glass pie plate.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Cut into serving portions.
Top each serving with scoop of vanilla ice cream.
Must be served hot.

title: five pounds of chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside. Combine sugar and evaporated milk in a buttered Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage or candy thermometer registers 234°; pour over chocolate morsel mixture.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer or wooden spoon until mixture thickens and begins to lose its gloss.
Stir in vanilla and chopped pecans.
Spread fudge evenly into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Chill until firm.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large ovensafe bowl.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar and beat in eggs.
Blend in orange juice and rind.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan which has been greased on the bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt the caramels with margarine and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Pour over the baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon remaining cake batter over the caramel layer; bake at 250° for 20 minutes and increase the temperature to 350°.
Bake for 10 minutes longer. Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until forms a ball.
Knead while still warm.
Keeps forever in covered container.

title: puntanesca
directions: Chop pasta al dente.
Chop tomatoes (coarsely), retaining fluid.
Drain tuna. Mix all ingredients, except olive oil.
When pasta is done, drain and rinse in hot water.

title: estofado-stew(serves 4)
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil in Dutch oven; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli; rinse. Add all chopped vegetables and olives; mix.
Add Parmesan cheese and dressing.
Best if prepared the night before serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with carrots and celery.
Great for parties.

title: anise cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oil together, then add eggs and anise.
Put all dry ingredients into a small bowl.
Alternate with the milk and flour mixture into the cream mixture until the batter is sticky enough to drop by level teaspoons on cookie sheets.
Cook cookies for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° until bottom of cookies are golden brown.
Tops will be white.
Let cool; frost and decorate.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and chocolate.
Gradually add 1 cup boiling water.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened and smooth.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Chill over ice water.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper in plastic bag.
Shake beef in bag to coat.
Brown in hot shortening in skillet.
Place meat in large baking dish or dutch oven.
Add soup, 2 cups of water, onion and basil.	Cover and bake at 375° for one hour.
Add vegetables and wine; bake for an additional hour or until tender.

title: whole grain quick bread
directions: Set aside 2 tablespoons cornmeal for topping.
Combine remaining dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add juice, honey, egg and oil.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into 8 cup ring mold.
Sprinkle reserved cornmeal over top.
Microwave on 80 for 7 to 8 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until bread tests done.
Remove from microwave and let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil breasts and layer in pieces in long casserole dish.
Cook broccoli 1/2 done and layer on top of chicken.
Mix together cream of chicken, cream of mushroom, mushrooms, lemon juice and Miracle Whip.
Spread on top of the broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese, then top with cracker crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve over cooked rice.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all of the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the boiling water.
Stir together.
When it's cool enough, put it on the table and knead it until it is thoroughly mixed.

title: chocolate gravy and biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and gradually add about 2 cups of milk.
Stir until mixed thoroughly (I taste to see if it's sweet enough), then set on heat.
Add a dash of vanilla.
Cook and stir constantly until gravy starts to thicken.
May have to add extra milk (my group likes it pretty thick).
Butter a pan of hot biscuits.
Open
up several biscuits on plate, then pour gravy over top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and both sugars together.
Add peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
Shape into small balls; roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Smash (make crisscross) with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Drain.
Top with catsup.
Return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Cook broccoli.
Using chicken broth, add margarine and flour to thicken, then add lemon juice and mayo.
Layer broccoli, chicken, sauce and cheese in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Split fryer down back. Salt and pepper chicken pieces and rub with flour. Place 1 1/2 sticks butter or margarine in roaster; melt in oven. Roll fryer in melted butter and place split side down. Add approximately 1 1/2 cups water. Bake at 350 degrees until done, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: icebox cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Spread in bottom of dish; bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
While crust is cooking, mix sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over cool crust.
Add fruit (well drained) at this point.
Mix pudding according to package directions and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Use the other 1/2 of Cool Whip for topping.
Chill and eat.
Delicious!!! Yields about 8 servings.

title: easy swedish pancakes
directions: Put eggs, flour, salt, sugar and 1 1/2 cups milk in large bowl.
Mix at medium speed until blended.
Add the 1/2 cup or more milk; batter should be thin.
Add 1/4 cup melted butter and blend. Preheat frypan (preferably electric) at highest temperature.
Put small amount of batter in pan; spread thin by tipping pan.
Turn when bubbly.
Do not overbake.
Roll and serve with butter, maple syrup or berry syrup and powdered sugar.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion and melted margarine.
Add salt and pepper.
Turn into a 1-quart greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: danish coffeecake
directions: Combine Bix-Mix and sugar in mixing bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in cream cheese and butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Add milk and stir until blended.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead 8 to 10 strokes.
On waxed paper, roll dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Carefully turn onto greased baking sheet and remove paper.
Spread preserves lengthwise down center third of dough.
Cut 1-inch strips along long sides of dough, cutting from filling out to edges.
Beginning at one end, fold strips at an angle across filling alternating from side to side.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Drizzle with Confectioners Glaze.

title: german sausage
directions: Fry sausage and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Melt jelly and mustard in saucepan.
Add sausages to jelly-mustard sauce and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: succotash
directions: Cut salt pork in cube size pieces and fry until lightly browned.
Remove pork from pan and stir in flour, mixing well. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic and simmer until tender.
Return salt pork to pan.
Add other ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: mom's chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine mashed potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can fried onions, mix thoroughly. Spoon potato mixture into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Using back of spoon, spread potatoes across bottom and up sides of dish to form shell.
In large bowl, combine chicken, green beans, soup, milk and seasoning; pour into shell.
Bake uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake uncovered 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: slime salad
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Place chopped chipped beef in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Wrap bacon around chicken breasts and place on top of beef.
Add mushrooms.
Mix together the soup and sour cream and pour on the chicken.
Add pepper.
Cover casserole with foil and bake 2 to 3 hours in slow oven, 350°.

title: chicken or steak teriyaki
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour over chicken or steak. Marinate at least 20 minutes.
Meat can then be grilled or broiled.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add Rotel and cook about 15 minutes.
Add crawfish tails (you may want to saute them in a little margarine
before adding to other ingredients, they will stay firmer).
Mix in rice, soup and parsley.
Pour into casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: linda's fruit salad
directions: Cook orzo; drain.
Mix sugar, juice, eggs, salt and flour. Boil until thick and creamy.
Pour mixture over orzo.
Set overnight.
Next day, add pineapple, oranges and Cool Whip.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, flour, soda, salt and juice of fruit cocktail. Beat well. Fold in fruit. Pour into three 8-inch round pans. Mix brown sugar, coconut and 1/4 cup chopped nuts. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend peanut butter, margarine and vanilla. Gradually add confectioners (powdered) sugar and powdered milk.
Use pastry blender to completely blend the mixture so that no white powder is seen.
Place in an 8-inch square pan.
Press with spoon to make solid.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon powdered sugar on top. Cut into serving pieces.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, Wesson oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: venison roast
directions: Rub seasoning on roast.
Mix liquids, pour over roast, cover and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Cook in oven at 200° all night long.
It's great.

title: chili cream cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and chili together.
Microwave about 3-4 minutes on high.
Add Cheddar cheese on top to melt.

title: lemon bread
directions: In large bowl, cream together butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add eggs and lemon peel to butter and sugar and beat well.
Adding a little at a time, mix flour mixture and milk into butter mixture, beating smooth after each addition until all milk and flour mixture has been added.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Take a toothpick and prick holes in bread.
Mix 3 teaspoons lemon juice with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour slowly over bread so mixture seeps in.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl combine potatoes, eggs, pickles, onions and green peppers.
Stir together mayonnaise, pickle juice, salt, pepper, celery seed and garlic salt.
Gently fold together both mixtures and chill.
Garnish with additional egg slices, if desired.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Mix together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar. Combine cake mixes, shortening and eggs together.
Shape into little balls and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. As cookies are coming out of oven, bounce to make cookies flatten. Cool and fill with cream cheese mixture.
Serve.

title: chicken with herbs and garlic
directions: Season chicken with salt and plenty of pepper.
Saute chicken in butter (using as little as possible).
Add garlic cloves (whole, chopped or use a press).
Sprinkle chicken with herbs and cover pan with a tight-fitting lid.
Cook over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
When tender, remove chicken and add several tablespoons wine or sherry.
(Water or juice is acceptable.)
Stir well with pan drippings; boil until liquid is reduced and pour over chicken.
Serve with noodles and steamed vegetables.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: First, put rice onto boil.
Cut tops off the tops of bell peppers and clean out the insides.
Boil peppers in plain water 8 to 10 minutes until soft.
Brown ground meat in butter.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons of the liquid.
Add onions and green onions and saute.
Sprinkle beef bouillon, basil, Tabasco, garlic salt and chili powder.
Add tomatoes, rice, cayenne pepper and grated cheese to meat sauce and mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture and place in a pan.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In blender or food processor combine undrained tomatoes, onion, garlic, cilantro and sugar.
Cover and blend until nearly smooth. Turn into a large saucepan; stir in chicken broth.
Bring to boiling; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all
ingredients.
Stir
in cream.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425°
for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake additional 50 minutes.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan combine the first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until all sugar is dissolved.
Gradually add milk and mix well.
Continue cooking until candy thermometer reads 248 degrees (firm ball stage).
Remove from the heat.
Stir in vanilla until blended.
Fold in the pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Spray waxed paper with cooking spray to prevent sticking.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in a microwave safe bowl or double boiler.
Drizzle over each cluster.
Cool.
Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble coarsely in large bowl 1/2 the cake.
Spread with 1/2 of pudding, 1 can pie filling, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 bananas and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Generously grease and flour one 10-inch Bundt pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, sift all dry ingredients together.
Add milk, olive oil, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly until batter is smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake on center rack 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sausage and wild rice
directions: Season with lemon pepper.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter; mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: jello salad
directions: Melt cream cheese. Add jello and pineapple.
Heat on low heat until mixture is completely dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator until it is thick.
Then add Cool Whip and put into a mold.
Set until firm. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: pasta salad with ziti noodles
directions: Cook ziti noodles according to box directions.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Now cook broccoli until done.
Place cut tomato, broccoli and seasoning to taste in with the pasta and toss with your favorite zesty Italian dressing.
This recipe is easy and great!!

title: salami
directions: Mix together hamburger and Morton Tender Quick and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, mix remaining ingredients with meat mixture and divide into 3 parts.
Roll each part into long rolls and wrap in nylon net and place on a wire rack in a pan and bake at 225° for 4 hours.
Wrap in a paper towel to absorb grease. Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: cranberry conserve(serves 8 to 12)
directions: Stir well, cover and chill.
The best Thanksgiving cranberry sauce!

title: layered english pea salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in a 2-quart bowl.
Mix the sour cream and mayo with the sugar and seasonings.
Spread over first 4 ingredients, sealing the edges.
Top with shredded cheese and bacon.
Chill.

title: salmon or tuna croquettes
directions: Preheat deep fryer at 350°.
Drain all, but 1/4 cup, liquid off the salmon or tuna and set that aside.
Put salmon or tuna in mixing bowl and break it apart with a fork until you have no big flakes.
Add the flour and egg.
You can add a dash of pepper, but no salt.
Mix well.
Add the baking powder to the liquid that was set aside and beat well with a fork or whisk until brothy.
(This is an important set and this mixture can't set.)

title: skewered beef with sa tsa chang
directions: Slice the beef into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Add soy sauce, cooking wine, 1/2 teaspoon water and cornstarch and mix well.
Mix Sa Tsa Chang, sugar, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 3 tablespoons water in a bowl for later use.
Divide the sliced beef into 6 portions. Insert the sliced beef through the 6 skewers.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork or pastry cutter, mix together first 4 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, beat remaining ingredients. Combine the two mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Then with hands, mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before rolling it into desired shape.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: lemon crust pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Add flavoring.
Add milk and flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: rosemary pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Rub roast or tenderloin liberally with olive oil, then spread the garlic over it.
Place in a 10 x 15 inch roast pan and sprinkle with rosemary.
Bake 375 for 2 hours or until the internal temperature of the pork reaches 160.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: marinara sauce with basil
directions: Saute garlic in oil until limp; add tomatoes and stir; simmer 5 minutes.
Add bouillon cube, mustard, salt, pepper, garlic powder and basil.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: scotch cake icing
directions: Five minutes before cake is done, place in saucepan used in making the cake.
Bring ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix and spread on cake while both are still hot.

title: legal chicken `n' pepper y'all
directions: Combine tomato juice, oregano, garlic powder, salt, pepper, artificial sweetener and dehydrated onion flakes in saucepan; simmer 1 hour or until reduced to 3/4 cup. Cool. Parboil peppers 3 minutes; drain. Combine 1/4 of mushroom and celery; add chicken. Mix well and spoon mixture evenly into peppers. Place peppers in casserole dish. Spoon 2 tablespoons of tomato juice mixture over each pepper. Place remaining tomato juice mixture over mushrooms. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Bake
vanilla
wafers
and
sugar
minutes at 350°. Blend softened
cheese
and
cup
sugar together in mixer. Prepare Dream Whip as package directions.
Place 1/2 of cheese mixture over
cooled
crust, add all pie filling.
Cover with last of cheese mixture and top with remaining 1/2 cup vanilla wafers. Chill.

title: my own white chili
directions: Boil chicken until tender; shred.
Save broth from boiled chicken.
Cook beans until tender; drain.
Add all ingredients to saved broth; simmer until flavors are blended.
Serve with white tortilla chips.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate raw potato and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot fat until brown.
Drain on paper towel. Serve with sour cream and applesauce.

title: baked mac and cheese
directions: Whiz the ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Add to 1 pound
of macaroni which has been cooked and drained.
Place mixture in a
sprayed
baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees and bake potatoes until fork tender. Potatoes can be cooked in microwave, instead.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Slowly blend in flour with a wire whisk until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add milk to the butter/flour mixture, whisking constantly.
Whisk in salt and pepper and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cut potatoes in half, scoop out the meat and set aside.
Chop 1/2 the potato peels and discard the remainder.
