When milk mixture is very hot, whisk in potatoes. Add green onion and potato peels.
Whisk well, add sour cream and crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese a little at a time until all is melted.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Very good dip for strawberries, cherries, white grapes, pineapple, cantaloupe, etc.

title: rolls
directions: Put yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar into the lukewarm water; dissolve and set aside.
Cream the sugar, Crisco and salt in a large
mixer
bowl.
Add the eggs and mix well.
Add the first mixture to the second.
Add 1 cup warm water and mix.
Beat in 4 cups of Gold Medal all-purpose flour gradually.
Knead dough until it
bounces
back.
Cover
and set in a warm spot.
Let double in bulk.
Punch down and make into Parker House rolls. (Cut
out with a biscuit cutter, dip in butter and fold over.) If mixture is too sticky to handle, place it in the refrigerator
for
a short time rather than adding too much flour.
Let rolls rise.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: peach pizza
directions: Mix margarine, flour and brown sugar well.
Press in pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Arrange sliced peaches over this.

title: crescent dogs
directions: Slit 8 hot dogs to within 1/2 inch of ends.
Insert 3 thin strips of American cheese in each slit.
Separate crescent dough into triangles and wrap dough over dog, keeping cheese atop. Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up.

title: aunt rosie's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream and mix first 6 ingredients well.
Set aside.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Set aside.
Mix together flour and baking powder. Set aside.
With creamed mixture, alternate adding milk mixture and flour mixture until both mixtures are used up.
Add flour to board and roll out to cut fairly thick.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste. Drain.
Cut Velveeta cheese into small squares.
Add to meat.
Add Ro-Tel.
Add taco seasoning.
Cook until melted.
Use milk to thin mixture, if necessary.
In individual servings, crunch chips into small pieces.
Add cheese and meat mixture to top.
Add salad toppings as desired.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, except oatmeal.
Mix it in, then add butter, eggs, milk and add raisins last.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bacon potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble, reserving 2 tablespoons
drippings in pan.
Remove pan from heat and add mayonnaise, mustard, sugar and salt, mixing well.
Combine potatoes, eggs, onions and celery in bowl.
Add dressing and toss. Stir in bacon pieces.
Chill several hours before serving. Serves 10.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pull thawed bread dough into walnut-size pieces.
Fill pan with single layer of dough balls.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat.
Pour over dough.
Let rise overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately onto foil lined cookie sheet.

title: pig pokin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil with mixer.
Beat in oranges and juice. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: green bean catalina
directions: Bundle 5 green beans and secure with bacon.
Place all bundles in a baking dish.
Cover with Catalina dressing and bake at 340° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in a flattened hump on plate. Cover with cocktail sauce.
Drain and wash shrimp and spread over sauce.
Top with green onions.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save juice for punch.
Take well drained fruit and add coconut, marshmallows and sour cream.
Cover and let set 24 hours before serving.

title: rose's mayonnaise cake
directions: Boil water and pour over nuts, raisins and soda.
Allow this mixture to cool.
Cream sugar and mayonnaise.
Add chocolate and cinnamon.
Stir together well.
Add flour slowly, alternating with water mixture, mixing well.
Put in greased and floured oblong pan and bake for 50 minutes in 350° oven or until done.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers until fine.
Pour in medium bowl.
Add raisins and nuts.
In saucepan, melt butter, syrup, cherries and juice and 1/2 bag of marshmallows.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs, raisins, rest of marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Press into buttered cake tin.
Put in refrigerator for 2 days before serving.

title: raeann's banana cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir first 5 dry ingredients; flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and baking soda.
Add next 5 wet ingredients; eggs, bananas, butter, buttermilk, and vanilla.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes, or until light and springy.
To be sure cake is done, use the toothpick test.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Measure flour; add potatoes.
Stir in eggs.
Mix well.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in squares.
Drop in boiling broth.
Be sure you stir each layer as you drop it in the boiling broth, because if you drop dry pot pie squares on top of dry layers, they will stick together and you will have lumpy pot pie.

title: chinese beef with broccoli
directions: Cut steak across grain into thin bite-size pieces.
Pour soy sauce and sherry over steak.
Sprinkle with cornstarch and sugar; mix well.
Cut broccoli into thin slices.
Peel stem; slice into 2-inch pieces.
Pour half the oil into a skillet or Dutch oven. Add salt and broccoli.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining oil and onion, stir well and add the steak.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli; mix thoroughly and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snicker brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine the cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and the melted butter.
Take 1/3 of the mixture and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased and generously floured pan.
(It helps to completely flour your hands when pressing the mixture.)
Bake for 6 minutes.

title: katie's frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; freeze in any size muffin cups.
After frozen, store in Ziploc freezer bags.
Kids of all ages enjoy this fruit treat with any meal!

title: rosamarina casserole
directions: Cook rosamarina in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Brown and drain onion and ground beef.
Combine pasta and beef mixture.
Add mushrooms, cheese, soup and milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles and cashews over top. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees, until browned lightly on top.
Approximately 1 hour.

title: kielbasa and noodle casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in large pot of lightly salted water.
Cook until water comes to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove potatoes and set aside. Add noodles to water and cook 5 minutes.
Drain and return to pot.
Heat butter and oil; add onion and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Add cooked potatoes, paprika and salt to onions.
Cook 2 minutes; add chicken broth and boil 1 minute.
Pour potato mixture over noodles and mix well.
Pour mixture in casserole.
Toss kielbasa over top.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: fried squash balls
directions: Boil squash with onion and salt to taste until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add next 3 ingredients and blend.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Shape mixture into balls.
Roll in cornmeal and fry in hot oil until brown.
Bell peppers, hot peppers and mushrooms are 3 fresh vegetables that can be frozen.
Place in plastic bag and store in freezer.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls, using 1/2 cup of mixture to make for each ball (about 25 balls). Place in a shallow baking dish and cover with soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
May also be rolled into golf ball size balls and cooked in crock-pot all day on low.

title: pasta puttanesca
directions: Drain tomatoes and chop coarsely.
Combine tomatoes and oil in a skillet and bring to boil.
Add remaining ingredients except pasta, one at a time, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat, allow sauce to thicken (15 to 30 minutes).
Serve over pasta.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Add orange juice and butter.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface roll to a 15 1/2-inch by 9-inch rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 3 strips, each 3 inches wide.
Divide sausage meat into thirds; roll each into a roll the length of the pastry.
Place each roll along one edge of a pastry strip.
Roll the pastry around the sausage.
Wet edges with ice water and press to seal tightly.
Chill the rolls for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut sausage rolls into 3/4-inch slices and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 12 minutes or until pastry is puffed and golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 60 appetizers.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cheese, Cool Whip and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry jello on top and fold into mixture.
Maraschino cherries and nuts may be added, if desired.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Saute onion in liquid from artichokes; add garlic.
Beat eggs; add cheese, pepper, Tabasco sauce, oregano, parsley and bread crumbs.
Stir in chopped artichokes to garlic and onion mixture. Stir everything together.
Bake in 11 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double lemon cake
directions: Mix together and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and while hot, prick with fork all over cake and spoon on carefully a mixture of lemon juice, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix well.

title: banana punch
directions: Freeze	together
blended
bananas, sugar water, orange and pineapple juice
and lemon juice.
Add 4 (6 ounce) cans of water. In punch bowl put frozen mixture, ice cream and ginger ale.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a skillet.
Add bell pepper and onions. Cook until tender.
Add
rice and broth.
Stir all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325 for 1 hour.

title: cabbage
directions: Chop up cabbage; cook in boiling salt water for just 7 minutes.
Cover with this sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and pecans; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 350° until filling is set.
(Can be divided into 2 pans.)

title: orange apricot freeze
directions: Mix well; spoon into muffin pan lined with cupcake liners. Freeze.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Remove frozen pastry from the package; allow to thaw at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice pastry into 1/2-inch wide x 4 1/2-inches long strips.
Brush with beaten egg.
Place pastry strips on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Twist each strip twice.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cocoa sigh cake(low-fat)
directions: In a small bowl mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
In a large bowl beat 3/4 cup sugar, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture and beat until evenly moistened.
In another large bowl and using clean, dry beaters, whip egg whites on high speed until frothy; gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar (1 tablespoon at a time) until stiff, moist peaks form.
Immediately add to cocoa mixture, gently folding in with a wire whisk until evenly blended.
Pour batter into a lightly oiled and floured 9-inch cheesecake pan (at least 3 inches deep) with removable rim.
Gently zigzag a spatula through batter; smooth top.
Bake in a 350° oven until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Cool on a rack (as cake cools, it settles and sinks slightly in center).
Remove pan sides. Spread cake top and sides evenly with Cocoa Frosting.
If made ahead, cover with a large bowl and chill up until next day.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello, water, 7-Up, pineapple, marshmallows and bananas. Let set until solid.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Combine juice, rind and egg; mix into dry ingredients.
Fold in berries and nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raspberry spritz(makes sixteen 6 ounce drinks)
directions: Puree the raspberries, sugar and lemon juice in a food processor or blender.
(It should make about 2 cups.)
Push through a fine sieve to remove the seeds.
The puree can be stored, tightly covered, in the refrigerator for 1 or 2 days or frozen for up to 3 months.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together except ginger ale. Add ginger ale at serving time.

title: fava beans with lamb(ful-eeyee ma' lahum ghanum)
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add onion and garlic and simmer.
Add beans and saute 5 more minutes.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cook in covered pan on low fire until beans are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch bars
directions: Grease and flour baking pan.
Beat eggs and sugar in bowl at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add fruit cocktail, flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Blend at medium speed until well blended.
Spread in pan and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
While hot, drizzle with glaze.
Cool and cut.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together and press onto a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, 10 or 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; adding sherbet last.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; stir in oil.
Add eggs; stir in carrots.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Layer bottom of 1 1/2-quart dish with bean dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Spread over bean dip.
Cover with grated cheese, then chopped tomatoes.
Onions are optional.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lazy blueberry pie
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix milk, 1 cup sugar and flour.
Pour over margarine.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to berries and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain the package of spinach well.
Add mayonnaise to bind. Use your own discretion as to dipping consistency.
Add onion and salt and pepper to taste.
A great dip for carrot sticks, celery sticks and cauliflower.

title: scents of the holidays(not to be eaten)
directions: Mix equal parts of Elmer's glue and liquid starch for a few minutes until smooth.
Do not cook.
Store covered.

title: pineapple cream dessert
directions: Prepare pudding as directed, omitting 1/2 cup milk.
Set aside at least 5 minutes.
Add softened cream cheese and whip until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over cream mixture.
Cover pineapple with Cool Whip.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough. Heat oven to 375°.
Using about 1 tablespoon of dough, shape around kiss and roll to make a ball.
Cover kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes, or until cookies are set, but not brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove to wire rack.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool; store in tightly covered container.
Roll in sugar again before serving.

title: chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Boil in a small amount of water, chopped celery and onion (until tender but not soft).
Drain well.
Prepare rice.
Mix together all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven until heated through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cream of celery and cream of chicken soup together and pour over cut up chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo with can of milk; pour over chicken.
Spread package of stuffing over mixture.
Pour 1 soup can of broth over this.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mizetti
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion, bell pepper, garlic salt and chili powder together.
Mix the soups, 1/2 the cheese and cooked noodles together.
Pour everything into a 9 x 13-inch
baking pan; top with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafers.
Put bananas on top.
Mix pudding with 1 3/4 cups milk.
Add 1 can Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on top of wafers and bananas.
Top with another 8 ounce bowl of Cool Whip.
Chill!

title: diet fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk then in cereal.
Bake in pan at 400° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: yam casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients and place in a greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: strawberry angel crumb cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake.
Add pineapple, strawberries, Cool Whip and ice cream.
Mix and freeze in Bundt pan.

title: cooks night out
directions: Open can of Vienna sausages. Do not lick bottom of lid.
Open package.
Place open can on edge of cracker paper.
Take alternating bites of cracker and Vienna sausages until both are gone.
Place lid in empty can.
Fold up cracker paper and place in can.
Discard can.

title: baked carrots
directions: Combine carrots, soup and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole and sprinkle on buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: laurie's famous cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put in a saucepan boiling water and butter.
Heat until butter melts.
Add all at once the flour.
Stir until dough forms a ball in center of the pan.
Remove from the heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time (important!!).
Beat until well blended after each egg added.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes or until brown, nut mushy.
After cooled, cut open and spoon out excess dough.
Mix whipping cream and pudding with electric mixer until stiff.
Spoon into cream puffs.
Top with melted chocolate bits.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add lemon juice, Tabasco sauce, mayonnaise, cream and salt. Mix thoroughly. Add shrimp, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Mix well. Serve on crackers or chips.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Set aside.
In separate bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture; mix well.
Pour small amounts of batter onto hot greased waffle iron.
Close lid quickly.
Do not open iron while cooking.
Remove waffle with fork.
Serve with fresh fruit or yogurt.
Makes 12 (4-inch size) waffles.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Place dry jello in warm pineapple with 1 envelope of gelatin (wet).
Cool.
Mix cottage cheese, almonds and whipped cream.
Chill.
Serve with mayonnaise and cherry on top.

title: tuna mold
directions: Heat soup almost to boiling point.
Add gelatin and stir. Soften cheese and have mayonnaise at room temperature (whip smooth) and add soup.
Add remaining ingredients and seasonings.

title: doug's mild "not wild" chili soup
directions: Cook ground beef; drain and set aside.
Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender, stirring frequently (do not brown).
Add next 8 ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low adding beef.
Simmer at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add beans (drained if preferred); heat.
Serve with tortilla chips and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: bologna gravy
directions: Melt butter/margarine.
Brown flour and diced bologna.
Add milk.
Stir until thickens.
Water may be added if too thick. Serve on toasted bread.
Good for breakfast or fast meal anytime.

title: lawana salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in freezer until ready to use.
May take out of freezer an hour before you use it.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix water and spaghetti sauce together.
Mix Mozzarella and cottage cheese together.
Brown ground beef and sausage; drain. Cover bottom of oblong pan with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Layer uncooked noodles on top.
Spread half of cheese mixture over noodles, then half of meat mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Repeat.

title: fish cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Shape in patties.
Fry in any type oil about 3 minutes on each side. Serves 6.
Can half the recipe.

title: magic peach pie
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan.
Mix milk, 1 cup sugar, flour and baking powder together well.
Pour in melted butter; do not stir. Pour fruit and 1 cup sugar in.
Do not stir any of this after you put ingredients on butter.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown at 375°.

title: low calorie whipped topping
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Stir milk powder into skim milk in saucepan.
Heat to simmering.
Add softened gelatin. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat with electric mixer or rotary beater until very thick and light.
Serve on fresh fruit.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add oats, Karo, vanilla and salt.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 14 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Mix peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Spread over baked oatmeal mixture.
Top with nuts.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light in color.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Stir in zucchini.
Add remaining dry ingredients including nuts. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or 4 to 5 cans at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain well.
Add tomatoes and simmer.
Add taco seasoning and dressing mix.
Simmer; then add pinto beans and corn.
Simmer, then serve.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: In iron skillet, brown hamburger.
Add other ingredients, except biscuits and cheese.
Stir.
Take off stove.
Cut biscuits in half; arrange in wagon wheel style around skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 4 not-so-hungry people.

title: red and black bean salad
directions: Pour both cans of beans into a colander to drain.
Pour the corn on top of the beans and drain well.
Pour the beans and corn into a 3-quart or larger bowl.
Finely chop onions and add them to the bowl.
Add Ro-Tel to the bowl.	To make the dressing pour the olive oil into a
2-cup glass measure.
Whisk in the vinegar, garlic powder, cumin, salt and pepper.
Pour the dressing over the bean mixture and stir until well coated.
Serve at once or chill until ready to serve.

title: aunt olive shafer's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs, flavoring and water. Stir in flour. Stir well. Cut up fruit and take 1/2 cup of the flour to mix into fruit. Mix all together with batter.

Bake in 300° oven for 3 or 4 hours in greased pans. Place pan of water in oven under cakes. You can use more or less fruit and nuts or whatever kind you want. Better baked ahead of time. Season with cloth soaked in apricot or peach brandy, then wrap and put in tight container or wrap in plastic wrap and aluminum foil for several weeks.

title: venison stew
directions: Sear venison until brown on all sides.
Add water.
Add celery, carrots, potatoes, onions and all other ingredients except frozen veggies.
Cook on medium until vegetables are tender and meat is cooked through.
Add frozen veggies and cook until hot. Remove bay leaf.
Serve with hard rolls.
May need to add additional broth.

title: cheesy vegetable dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the vegetables; chill. Serve the dip with a variety of raw vegetables.

title: spiced cranberry relish
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and chop.
Mix together the soup, onion, egg, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add chopped broccoli.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain; season.
Put 1 can chili in bottom of pan, then cheese, meat and rest of chili.
Beat rest of ingredients and pour over chili, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Chop and combine first 3 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; heat and then cool.
After sugar-vinegar-salt-celery-mustard seed mixture cools, pour over cabbage mixture; package and freeze.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix hot water with box of jello.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 350°.
Drizzle with powdered sugar mixed with lemon juice.

title: eggplant-tomato sauce
directions: Heat
oil
in a 6 quart saucepan over medium heat for 3 minutes or until hot.
Add eggplant, mushrooms, onion, parsley and garlic.
Saute 10 minutes or until tender.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put in microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes. Remove. Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup peanut butter. Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.

title: chocolate butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add melted chocolate and vanilla and blend in flour to make a stiff dough. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Dip in slightly beaten egg white; roll in pecans. Put on greased cookie sheet. Press cookie top with fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fried yams
directions: Scrub the potatoes and boil for 10 minutes.
Peel and cut into slices.
Add to hot oil and fry until lightly browned.
Remove and drain.
Add salt and serve.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add oats, tomato sauce, spinach, egg, seasonings and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Pack half of this mixture into baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Next, layer tomatoes and remaining meat mixture over tomatoes.
Top with remaining Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: gumdrop fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix well the creamed butter, sugar and well beaten eggs.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt; reserve 1/4 cup for coating gumdrops.
Add sifted mixture to first mixture alternately with the applesauce.
Blend together the baking soda and hot water; add to mixture.
Add the vanilla, raisins, nuts and gumdrops (which have been coated with the reserved dry mixture).
Dough will be very stiff.
Bake in a greased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Good to eat fresh or store in a tin.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together the first 3 ingredients in saucepan over low to medium heat.
Drizzle over Rice Chex and gently stir until coated. Put powdered sugar in large paper grocery bag; shake until sides are coated.
Put mixture in bag and shake until all Rice Chex are coated with the powdered sugar.

title: apricot jello delight
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until melted.
Add cold water.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, cut up bananas fine.
Add pineapple. Pour the jello mixture over fruit and jell.

title: white wine  glaze
directions: Boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes then spread over cool cake.

title: california dip
directions: In small bowl, mix soup mix and sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers, or pretzels and chips.

title: krista's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars, add eggs, vanilla and water and blend till smooth.
In another bowl blend flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry to wet ingredients and mix well.
Add oats until all oats are moist.
Add chips and chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake at 350 F for 13 minutes.
Remove when center is slightly moist.

title: mexican bread
directions: Spread Frito bean dip on round tortilla chips. Top with Colby cheese.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese melts.

title: grammie jean's cowboy cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla; set aside.
Mix together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add the first mixture to this mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet by rounded spoonfuls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss cheese mushroom pie
directions: Note:
If you use the food processor, things go fast.

title: grilled salmon with tarragon mayonnaise
directions: Combine first six ingredients and blend well.
Cover and chill 2 to 4 hours.
Top each salmon steak with 2 tablespoons of tarragon mayonnaise and grill for 4 to 6 minutes.
Repeat for other side. Arrange on serving platter and garnish with lemon slices.
Pass remaining tarragon mayonnaise.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix sugar, cake mix, sour cream and oil.
Beat until creamy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured tube pan.

title: squash pie
directions: Combine squash, spices and sugar. Mix well.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's best popsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients until dissolved.
Add 2 cups of cold water.
Pour into popsicle holders.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: texas pie
directions: In greased pan, spread apple pie filling and pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Cut up margarine over cake mix. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad(serves 10)
directions: Boil eggs.
Boil potatoes with skin on until tender; drain. Let cool and peel while still warm.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper while potatoes are still warm.
Marinate for 15 minutes.
Peel and chop all but one egg.
Mix eggs with chopped potatoes.
Add more salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Keep corn hot in 250° oven.
Melt butter, stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla. Pour over corn, mix well.
Turn into large shallow roasting pan. Bake 1 hour in 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes.
When cool, break in pieces.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and pepper in oil until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Sprinkle onions and cucumbers with 1 tablespoon salt.
Cover and put into refrigerator for 1 hour then drain.
Heat to a boil sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
After mixture comes to a boil, pour over drained cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 325° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Recipe will be gooey. If it is real gooey, bake a little longer.

title: karyn's monkey bread
directions: Thaw dough in refrigerator overnight.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cut chicken in strips or nuggets.
Let chicken sit in egg batter for 1 hour.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Brown in margarine; place in casserole dish.
Add mushrooms, lemon juice and broth. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine broth, onions and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, stir together milk and flour.
Stir into broth mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in corn. Heat through.
If desired, sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet pepper

title: peachy keen slush
directions: In saucepan, boil sugar and 2 cups water for 3 minutes, cool. In nonmetal container combine sugar mixture, concentrates, 3 cups water, schnapps and lemon juice.
Cover and freeze.
Spoon 1/2 cup slush into glass, stir in 1/2 cup ginger ale.

title: cheesy zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all.
Bake in ungreased 2-quart dish, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: "morning after" baked oatmeal
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and mix.
Add the next 4 ingredients; mix.
Pour into an 8-inch round by 2-inch deep baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with milk; top with fresh fruit (sliced peaches, sliced strawberries, blackberries, etc.).

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cut crab-flavored fish into bite size pieces; set aside.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, raisins, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Spoon into bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch casserole dish.
In medium bowl, combine 2 cups flour, brown sugar and salt; cut in margarine very coarsely.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: dill sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature 1 hour to allow flavors to blend.
Use as dip for chicken nuggets.
Makes 1 cup.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles.
(Breaking noodles into 2 inch pieces saves cooking time.)
When cooled, mix all together.
Marinate overnight.

title: sticky cinnamon buns
directions: Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and raisins.
Partially thaw bread dough.
Cut each loaf into 8 slices and each slice into 4 pieces.
Line pan in rows with pieces.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the top of the bread pieces.
Cover and let rise until double in size or overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Immediately invert buns onto platter.
Enjoy!

title: oriental grilled roast
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Put the roast in a shallow pan and pour the soy sauce mix over it; let stand overnight.
Grill the roast until done using the marinade as a baste.
Slice and serve.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Heat milk and butter together until scalded; add to batter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Batter is very liquidy.)

title: bratwurst casserole
directions: Cut bratwurst in chunks.
Brown, but do not cook until done. Slice onions and potatoes into a baking dish.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt; remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8 to 9-inch square pan.
Chill for 2 hours, or until firm.
Remove from pan; cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.
Can be stored at room temperature.

title: baked rice with mushrooms
directions: Cut up the onions and saute in butter.
Add mushrooms with liquid and beef consomme.
Add rice (Comet) well washed (raw). Mix well and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Cover casserole with aluminum foil while cooking.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and pineapple together in blender. Add to other ingredients.
Pour into dish or salad mold to chill.

title: caramel frosted cinnamon rolls
directions: Prepare cinnamon rolls.
Then heat butter in an iron spider. Add sugar and water.
Let cook 1 minute in spider.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Then cool, cut the roll into equal parts, about 1-inch thick.
Place close together, cut side down, in spider. Let rise until light and bake 20 minutes in moderate oven at 350°, until golden brown.
Invert the spider, remove rolls.

title: tater junctions
directions: After baking potato, slice potatoes horizontally.
Fluff up the potatoes.
Top your your favorite hamburg stroganoff.
Top with cheese.
Place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour remainder of stroganoff in bowl to add at table.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Put 1 teaspoon of butter on chicken breast and sprinkle with lemon pepper and salt. Place in baking dish; cover and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out. Mix soup, water and more lemon pepper together and heat on stove. Pour chicken broth out of baking dish. Mix well with soup mixture. Add 1 1/2 cups rice to chicken and pour in baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes more.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put spinach in a salad bowl.
Chop the hard-boiled egg; add to spinach.
Crumble the bacon and add the bacon and sliced mushrooms to the bowl.
Sprinkle this with the Parmesan cheese.
Add the salad dressing right before serving.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Stir together oats, flour, cheese and margarine.
Press into 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy spinach noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Pour melted butter over noodles. Stir in sour cream, milk, mushrooms, parsley and Parmesan.
Rinse frozen salad shrimp under cold water; drain and combine with noodles.
Warm casserole in a 350° oven or in microwave for 5 minutes.
Ready to serve (4 to 6).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chill in Ziploc bag.

title: pita bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup lukewawrm water and let rise about 10 minutes in warm place.
In a large bowl, place the flour, salt and yeast mixture.
While stirring, gradually add the remaining water.
Lightly flour working surface and knead dough until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Let rise in towel-covered bowl in warm place until doubled in size (about 2 hours).
Knead again for a few minutes.
Divide in about 20 balls and shape each one into pita form (about 1/2-inch thick) on floured board.
Place pitas on cloth-covered table, slightly apart, and cover with second cloth.
Let rise again (about 1 hour).
Bake several minutes in a preheated 425° oven until golden brown. Yield:
20 pitas.

title: copper pennies
directions: Prepare at least one day in advance.
Cook carrots until just tender.
Remove and drain.
In saucepan, put soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Put carrots, onion and peppers in container with top.
Pour marinade over.
Cover and refrigerate. Will keep 2 weeks.

title: "gooey" chocolate cake
directions: In a saucepan, melt oleo, cocoa and water; bring to a boil. In separate bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Pour the boiling chocolate mixture into flour and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake 20 minutes in a moderate oven (350°), then ice with icing.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine cornbread, squash, onion, margarine, egg and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well and bake for 30 minutes.

title: new york all purpose mix
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mix is consistency of cornmeal.
Store in covered container at room temperature.
To measure, spoon lightly into cup; level off with knife.
Do not pack.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter. Keep over heat and add soup, cheese and flour. Stir with a wire whisk until it boils. Add broth. Blend. Remove from heat. Add remaining ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole for 30 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: all-in-one hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Put into large casserole dish.
Add 2 potatoes (cut up) for each person being served.
Add corn, cream of mushroom soup and vegetable beef soup.
Add mushrooms (if desired).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Mix together by hand the first 4 ingredients and put in a long pan.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until they are tender-crisp.
Add peas and next ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for about 20 minutes, stir.
Serve.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until almost done.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook until vegetables are done (not mushy).
Add celery soup and heat well.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: creole fish
directions: Season fish with salt, pepper, vinegar and thyme.
Fry in margarine; take out when half done.
Fry onion and yam in same margarine until brown; add water and tomato slices.
Let cook for 10 minutes; add fish and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 4.

title: mock crab dip
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and soup.
Cook 30 minutes on low heat.
Season with salt, red pepper and garlic powder.
Add tuna or crab meat and juice of 1/2 lemon.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Serve in chafing dish with Ritz crackers.

title: divine chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
In a separate dish, combine pepper, butter, garlic and salt.
Dip chicken in butter mixture, then in crumb mixture.
Roll into firm roll and skewer with toothpick.
Arrange in a 12 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Drizzle remaining butter over chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at Medium-high 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
This dish may be prepared ahead of time and reheated.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter.
Press evenly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all oil and all dressing together.
Put all crackers and oil mix in bowl.
Slop around (2 to 4 ounces of oil mix left over in bowl).
Don't soak crackers.
Bake on cookie sheet 1 hour and 15 minutes at 225°.
Dump on paper towels to absorb excess oil.

title: party sandwich mix
directions: Mix together and mold.

title: hot broccoli cheese dip
directions: Mix all together in baking dish.
Bake at 350°, until bubbling occurs.
Use carrot sticks, Sociables crackers or bread sticks to dip.

title: spiced beef brisket
directions: Place beef in a 3 1/2 to 4-quart crockery cooker.
Combine 2 cups of water, soup mix, ketchup, Worcestershire, cinnamon, garlic and pepper.
Pour over beef.
Cover; cook on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove beef; keep warm.
Pour cooking liquid into a glass measure.
Skim off fat.
Transfer 3/4 cup liquid to a moisture and vaporproof container.
Cool slightly.
Seal.
Label and freeze for up to 6 months.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place flour in medium bowl; pour corn oil in measuring cup.

Add buttermilk, flour and oil to mixture; add all at once, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out on floured surface and knead dough 3 or 4 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter, place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice until almost tender.
Fry bacon until crisp. Remove from pan and drain grease.
Saute onion and celery until transparent.
Set aside.
Brown ground chuck and drain grease again.
Add rest of ingredients (except rice) and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add to cooked rice and put into casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 325°.
If it looks too dry, add a little more water and stir.
When serving, some people like a little garlic salt sprinkled on individually.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients (except crackers) and pour into casserole dish. Cover top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over top of crackers.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes uncovered.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain the water off of the beans.
Put in a large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight or until chilled really well.

title: chunky style applesauce
directions: Put all ingredients in slow cooker, cover and set on low and cook 8 to 10 hours.
Serve warm with or without cream.

title: fresh peach pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart deep baking casserole dish. Combine 1 cup of sugar, flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Pour 1 cup of sugar over peaches; let stand 30 minutes or more. Combine milk or fruit juice with eggs; pour over melted butter. Add fruit and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nalesniki
directions: Have ready one or more heavy 6-inch frypans, lightly buttered and well heated.
Put eggs in blender and blend.
Add sugar, salt, flour and milk and blend thoroughly.
Pour enough batter into buttered, heated pans to cover the bottom of the pan by tilting and swirling it around the bottom.
Shape the pancakes over the heat until they are slightly brown.
Turn once and let brown. Roll up with jelly.
Yields 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: company chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water for 1 1/2 minutes only. Do not overcook.
Cool quickly in ice water and drain on paper towels.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Use a large bowl.
Fix broccoli and cauliflower into small florets.
Cut mushrooms in half.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and wine vinegar and pour over vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.
Enjoy!

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix all except oil. Blend 10 seconds. Add oil. Blend 10 seconds. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 1 cup.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix flour in milk and bring to a boil; slowly stir in butter, salt and pepper.

title: chocolate cream drops
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: gumdrop nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, egg, milk and Bisquick.
Beat vigorously.
Batter may be slightly lumpy.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Bake in five well-greased soup cans 40 minutes.
When bread is done toothpick stuck into center comes out clean.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Combine marshmallows and pineapple.
Let sit for 8 hours or overnight, unrefrigerated.
Stir in heavy cream and refrigerate until serving.
Stir before serving.
Can be doubled.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer beans in glass baking dish; sprinkle taco seasoning mix on beans.
Smash and spread avocados on top.
Next, sprinkle on tomatoes and onions, then spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle on grated Cheddar cheese, then top with sliced olives and serve with Doritos.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Consistency should be moist, not too dry.
This recipe makes 3 shells for 9-inch pie plate.
Fill shells or make 2 shell pie.
Bake as needed.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken in crock-pot.
Mix the soup and mushrooms until well combined, mixing in sour cream.
If cooking on low, pour over chicken and cook for 6 to 8 hours.
If cooking on high, cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours and add sour cream the last 30 minutes. Serve with noodles or rice.

title: skunk odor remedy(when your dog loses the battle with a skunk)
directions: Pour over dog & leave for 10 minutes. Then rinse.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies well.
Mix sugar and cream cheese until smooth. Mix milk and pudding.
Add pudding to sugar and cheese mixture.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Combine sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs; lemon flavoring and buttermilk.
Add remaining dry ingredients with one cup flour to first mixture.
Add additional flour to make a dough; just stiff enough to toss on floured board; roll out and cut.
Fry in deep fat.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Spread all but 1 1/2 cups dough on ungreased jelly roll pan.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Spoon extra dough on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing while still warm.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Sift 3	cups
flour,
cinnamon,
soda,	salt and baking powder in a
bowl.
Beat
eggs well in bowl.
Gradually add sugar and oil
and
mix well.
Add vanilla to the dry ingredients also and beat well.	Stir in zucchini.
Combine nuts with flour.
Stir
in butter.
Pour
into
3 greased, floured loaf pans.	Bake at
350° for 1 hour, or until tests done.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: fancy jello
directions: Boil water.
Divide the ice cream into four sections. Dissolve 1 pkg. jello in 1 cup boiling water in large bowl.
Add 1/4 of the ice cream.
Stir until ice cream is melted.
Pour in glass bowl.
Chill until firm.
Repeat for each package of jello until you have four layers of different colors in bowl.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix ice cream, Cool Whip and crushed Oreos together.
Freeze in a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Cut into squares.
Top with chocolate sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Combine rice and broccoli and put in greased casserole dish.
Heat milk, undiluted soup and Cheez Whiz until mixed.
Pour over broccoli/rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water to firm boiling stage.
Add peanuts.
Continue to cook, stirring constantly until mixture is light brown or hard crack stage.
Stir in butter, salt and soda. Pour in buttered baking dish while still foamy.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Spray an ovenproof casserole dish with Pam.
Mix the chicken, chilies, olives, soup and sour cream together.

title: ham puff casserole
directions: Place the milk and butter in a saucepan; bring to boiling point. Stir in cornmeal slowly and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in beaten egg yolks, salt and paprika. Add the cheese and stir until melted. Add the ham and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bread bread into small pieces.
Place in mixing bowl with 1 cup sugar, evaporated milk, milk, vanilla, egg yolks and melted butter.
Mix well; pour into 10 x 8 x 2-inch size baking pan. Bake in preheated oven, 450° for 15 minutes.
Remove and make meringue.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Cover pudding with meringue and rebake for 3 or 4 minutes until meringue is golden.
Serves 12.
May be served with rum sauce, if desired.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Put crumbles on crust (save 1/4 cup).
Top with prepared pudding; let set in refrigerator until firm, about 30 minutes.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbles.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut apples in quarters.
Peel apples and remove cores.

Slice apples in thin slices and put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix oats, sugar and flour. Add butter and stir until crumbly mixture. Put mixture on apples and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Boil potatoes in 7 quarts of water in 12-quart pan.
Add to potatoes, onion, caraway seed, salt and garlic.

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix butter, egg yolks, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together. Put a layer of cake and top with mixture.
Crush Butterfinger candy bars on top of this.

title: restaurant country style steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides in shortening just until brown (not done).
Place meat in casserole dish.
Cover the steak with water. Take grease used in browning steak and add salt, pepper and flour.
Let flour get dark with heating.
Pour this mixture into steak and water.
Cover with tinfoil.
Cool 1 hour at 350° or until tender.
Gravy will thicken with cooking.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil together, add pumpkin and dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 325° for one hour and fifteen minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in a large casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Make a well in dry ingredients; pour eggs, milk and oil into well; mix.
Stir in coconut, cherries, carrots, pecans and raisins.
Pour mixture into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, oatmeal, baking powder and baking soda. Add chips, candy and nuts. Roll into walnut size ball.
Place about 2-inches apart.
Makes about 112 cookies.

title: inside-out pizza(child's recipe)
directions: Roll out each loaf until flattened.
Spread half of each loaf with half of the Ragu.
Sprinkle each loaf with 1 bag of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese. Fold in half and seal edge of each pizza (sort of like a big pierogi).
Bake on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, or until cooked through.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: millionaire pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix milk and juice together.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into pie crust.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Combine meats, bread crumbs, eggs, onions and seasonings; mix lightly.
Shape into medium size balls and brown in oleo.
Place in casserole.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Boil butter and sugar 2 1/2 minutes.
Line cookie sheet with foil (shiny side up).
Butter lightly.
Place whole soda crackers completely (line) over bottom.
Pour butter, sugar mixture over top.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesed cauliflower
directions: Stir sour cream and 1/4 cup cheese into drained cauliflower. Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: tom's fundraising chicken chili
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut tomatoes into 1-inch pieces; reserve liquid. Cut chicken breasts into small pieces; pour tomato liquid over chicken and bake 20 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bake for 90 minutes or simmer on stove top for 1 hour.
Serve hot over brown or white rice.
Top with sour cream and scallions.
Serves 10.
Only 2 ounces of fat in each serving!

title: frosted cranberry cream salad
directions: Combine pineapple, cranberry sauce, sour cream and pecans. Turn into 8 x 8-inch pan, cover and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer a few minutes ahead of serving time.
Cut in squares; serve on salad greens.
Yields 9 servings.

title: sicilian seafood chowder
directions: Heat oil, onion, celery and pepper.
Saute until tender for about 7 minutes.
Add garlic, basil, thyme, pepper, oregano and cayenne pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add clam juice and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until slightly thickened (about 30 minutes).
Add shrimp, scallops and crab to chowder and cook until shrimp are pink.
Cook orzo pasta until tender, but still firm.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Drain again.
Add orzo, clams and parsley.
Stir until heated and serve.
Great with Italian bread and garden salad.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Cream well the cream cheese and sugar.
Whip Dream Whip as usual; add sugar.
Fold Dream Whip into cream cheese.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Spread cherry pie filling over top.

title: rainbow dessert
directions: Mix 1 box of jello with 1 cup boiling water, then mix in blender with 1/4 of half gallon frozen yogurt.
Pour in bowl. Repeat with remaining boxes.
Put in four layers, using each box as a layer.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Add sugar, butter and salt to milk and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast (dissolved in a little water) and 1 egg.
Sift flour and cinnamon together and add to liquid with candied fruit and currants.
Mix well.
Cover and let rise to double.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Saute or microwave butter, garlic, green pepper and onion. Mince mushrooms and add to sauteed mixture.
Add enough bread crumbs to make consistency spreadable.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Add chopped onions, wine and water. Simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms, salt and artichoke hearts. Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve with noodles sprinkled with parsley.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, cheese and raisins. In a small bowl, blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour sauce over broccoli mixture.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: pepperoni puffs
directions: Flatten biscuits one by one with a small glass.
Put 3 slices of pepperoni and slice of cheese in center of biscuit.
Pinch biscuit closed around cheese and pepperoni.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm with hot spicy mustard.

title: easy brownie pizza
directions: Grease and flour 12 x 1/2-inch pizza pan (or two 9-inch layer cake
pans).
In
3 quart saucepan bring corn syrup and heavy cream
to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add chocolate;
stir
until melted.
Set aside 2/3 cup of the chocolate
sauce.
Add
butter
and
sugar to remaining sauce; stir
until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually
stir
in flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake
at
for
minutes or until firm.
Cool on rack.
(Cool
layers
in
pans
10 minutes, remove and cool on racks.)
Top
with ice cream, fruit, nuts and chocolate sauce. Makes 12 servings.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Bring to a boil the last 4 ingredients; let cool before pouring over other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: peanuts crispy cookies
directions: Cream together until light the butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Grease bottom of tumbler.
Dip in granulated sugar and use to flatten cookies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove at once to wire racks to cool.
Store airtight or freeze.

title: chicken and tamale casserole
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
When chicken is cool, tear into chunks.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch squares.
Mix soups, milk, onion, salsa and 2 tablespoons broth.
In large casserole, layer 1/2 the tortillas.
Cover with 1/2 the chicken chunks and 1/3 of the sauce.
Repeat tortillas, chicken and 2/3 of the sauce.
Let set for 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with streusel.

title: white christmas chiffon pie
directions: Bake a 9-inch pie shell.
Soften the gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix together in saucepan 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Stir constantly until it boils; boil 1 minute.
Stir in the softened gelatin; cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix flour, salt and soda in a separate bowl.
Add flour and mashed bananas alternately to the sugar mixture.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese, eggs and Bisquick together.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake until done.
Pour off grease and serve.

title: chocolate toffee bars
directions: Arrange grahams in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
In 1-quart casserole dish, microwave butter and brown sugar on High for 2 minutes. Stir well.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Spread evenly over grahams.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Let stand a few minutes, then spread chocolate over bars.
Cut when cool.

title: easy shrimp dinner
directions: Heat sauce. Add shrimp and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil or bake sweet potatoes and cream potatoes, butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon, vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in milk; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: toasted turkey buns
directions: Split buns, use tops for turkey buns and save bottoms for bread crumbs.
Combine turkey, celery, seasonings and mayonnaise. Top buns with butter, 1/2 ham slice, a scoop of turkey salad and top with grated cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cream of tartar, salt and baking powder 4 times.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to egg whites and beat until standing up, but not stiff.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Pour in ungreased pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 40 minutes. Cool before removing from pan.

title: creamy louis dressing
directions: Stir together 1 cup mayonnaise, 1/3 cup sweet pickle relish, 3 tablespoons finely chopped green pepper and 1/8 teaspoon liquid hot pepper seasoning.
Whip 1/2 cup whipping cream until stiff; gently fold into mayonnaise mixture until thoroughly blended. Cover and chill.
Makes about 2 cups dressing.

title: mile high pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy. Add berries (undrained), sugar and juice. Beat at high speed with your mixer for 15 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Pile high on cooled pie shell and freeze for several hours. However, all day or overnight is better. Serve frozen directly from the freezer and it will not taste frozen.

title: old fashioned southern green beans
directions: Combine the green beans, water, and salt pork in a large saucepan. My mother used to cook green beans in an iron pot. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until beans are tender and most of the water has cooked out.
This will probably take about an hour. Add oil and mix.
Taste and add black pepper and salt, if needed.
Some salt pork is more salty than other. If the salt pork is not sliced, cut several slits in the chunk of salt pork, cutting almost all the way through.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix well the vanilla pudding and milk, then add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Stir.
Layer wafers, bananas and filling in a large dish, ending with filling on top.
Sprinkle with wafer crumbs.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream brown sugar, sugar, Crisco and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk, flour and baking powder, starting and ending with flour.
Add black walnuts. Pour into greased and floured (10-inch) tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: buttermilk puffs(doughnuts)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Add shortening and then egg.
Beat until smooth. Drop by teaspoon into hot fat (375°).
Fry until brown, turning from one side to the other.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll in granulated sugar while still warm.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into loaf in a baking dish.
Make sure meat does not touch sides of dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Top with mixture of 1/2 cup ketchup and 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Let meat loaf stand, covered, 5 minutes before slicing.

title: poached chicken in white wine
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Add chicken, wine and parsley; season well.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Add mushrooms and cucumber; season again.
Cover and continue cooking 6 to 7 minutes.

title: chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chili powder, dry mustard, corn, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: love letters
directions: Combine chicken, green onions, cheese, garlic and onion powders and salt in a medium size bowl.
Mix well.
Place wrappers on counter with a corner facing you.
Put 1 teaspoon chicken mixture slightly below center of wrapper and fold bottom of corner up.
Fold sides in, points overlapping, and wet edges to seal. Deep fry, a few at a time, until golden brown and crispy around edges.
Drain and serve hot.

title: shrimp and linguine alfredo
directions: Boil noodles to texture.
Boil shrimp until pink.
Boil alfredo cheese sauce as per directions on package.
Mix together in large pot.
Serves 2 people.

title: claude's crunchy chicken
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Dip chicken in mixture, coating heavily and then dip into stuffing mix, again coating heavily. Roll pinwheel fashion and place in baking dish.
Pour melted butter on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared well ahead of baking time.

title: easy breakfast casserole(great for brunches)
directions: Cook and drain bacon, sausage or ground beef.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt, mustard and cheese.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place slices of bread in pan.
Put meat on top.
Pour egg mixture over the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in morning at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low calorie vegetable dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add buttermilk until of dripping consistency. Chill well and serve with raw vegetables.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Chop cabbage and pack loosely in sterilized quart jars.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Pour boiling water over cabbage, one jar at a time.
Seal at once.
Keep water boiling as you fill each jar and seal.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion soup
mix, eggs, cracker crumbs and milk together.
Then mix remaining ingredients separately.
Put 1/2 of mixture into
the
meat loaf mixture and put the rest on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pigs-n-the blankets
directions: Grease baking pan.
Turn oven to 350°.
Open biscuits; set aside.
Open hot dogs; cut in half.
Roll up in the biscuit dough. Place on pan; let cook for about 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown crisp or done.
Let cool; serve with mustard and ketchup.

title: squash skillet medley
directions: Heat margarine or oil in skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute lightly.
Add sliced squash and other ingredients, ending with tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle seasonings over tomatoes.
Stir through. Cover and cook about 20 minutes until squash is tender but not overcooked.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese or several slices of cheese if you prefer.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar well, then add cocoa and vanilla; stir. Add oatmeal.
Roll into balls and dip in powdered sugar.
Ready to eat.
No baking!

title: hot tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, chili seasoning mix and sliced olives.
Simmer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil the chicken breast halves until done.
Cook the rice in chicken broth.
Drain rice and add the soups.
Mix with cut up chicken and rice.
Put in casserole dish and bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pottawattamie county rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add half the mixed flours plus all the brown sugar, salt, shortening and caraway seed.
As you mix, stir in remaining flour vigorously. Turn over twice in large, greased mixing bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Stir about 1/2 minute.
Cut up and shape into loaves, using greased pan.
Bake at 375° about 50 minutes.
Brush with shortening.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Add onion and bell pepper. Bake in oven until tender and slightly browned (350° to 400°).
Spread soup over pork chops evenly. Sprinkle corn bread crumbs over the soup. Bake until bubbly and golden brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or golden mushroom soup

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Put all this in a large saucepan and boil about 10 minutes. Put in 2 1/2 to 3-quart buttered casserole dish and cook with cover on it in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In a large pot (approximately 10-quart), cook meat, onion and green peppers; drain.
Add garlic, green chilies, chili powder, vinegar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste and juice from kidney beans.
Heat until boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans and simmer an additional 30 minutes.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Put steak in freezer until partially frozen.
Slice diagonally into 1/8-inch slices.
In bowl combine steak and 4 tablespoons cornstarch; mix well.
Add 4 tablespoons soy sauce, put in refrigerator 30 minutes or longer.
Peel carrots and slice diagonally in 1/4-inch slices.
Cook carrots about 5 minutes.
Chop onion and green pepper in bite size pieces.
Set aside.

title: pickled fish
directions: Cut fish into small pieces. Cover with cold water and add three Tbsp of salt. Let soak for
two hours. Drain fish well and place side by side in a pan. Add spices and vinegar enough
to cover.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: sparkling cherry party punch
directions: To freeze strawberries, blueberries and grapes, wash and gently pat dry.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking pan. Freeze until firm.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle crumbled bacon or ham and cheese in pie shells.
Beat remaining ingredients until blended and pour over cheese and bacon. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Cut into wedges and serve hot.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Combine and boil to soft ball stage.
Pour 2 cups walnuts into mixture and stir until coated.
Spread on foil and separate.

title: potato mushroom casserole
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes and onion about 1/8-inch thick. In a large baking dish, arrange onion and potato slices in a layer.
Place chips of butter on top.
Pour the can of soup on top.
Pour 1/2 can of water on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Pour into butter and cocoa mixture.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cover hot cake with marshmallows cut in half, cut side down, pressed lightly into cake.

title: banana pudding
directions: In double boiler, mix well and cook until thick.
Have ready in a container, crumbled vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour the thick mixture over this and mix.
Beat egg whites and spread over this.
Brown in oven.

title: 12-egg sponge cake
directions: Beat the 12 egg yolks until thick; add the sugar gradually until you have a rich, thick mixture.
Add lemon juice, lemon rind and orange juice and continue beating.
Sift the matzoh cake meal, potato starch and salt together three times; fold in lightly. Beat the egg whites until they stand in peaks, but be sure you stop before they look dry (very important!).
Gently fold into the cake batter.
Line bottom of an 8 x 14-inch pan with waxed paper or oiled brown paper.
Pour in the batter and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Invert on cake rack to cool before removing from pan.

title: bittersweet chocolate sauce
directions: Gradually stir milk into cocoa in small saucepan.
Add margarine; cook over medium heat just to simmering, stirring frequently.
Stir in vanilla; cool.
Stir in NutraSweet Spoonful; refrigerate.
Serve chocolate sauce over frozen yogurt or sliced fruit.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan, then pour package of hash browns into pan.
Mix together soup, onions, cheese, salt, pepper and sour cream and pour over potatoes.
Then mix melted stick of butter and Rice Krispies and spread on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broiles
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on rye bread slices and garnish with a slice of olive.
Broil until golden brown.

title: baked herb seasoned chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Top with Swiss cheese. Combine soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: thanksgiving punch
directions: Chill ingredients. Mix in Punch bowl adding 7-up last.
Add a few drops of red food coloring, orange slices & lemon Slices.

title: chuck wagon casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender. Add corn, tomato paste and water; heat, then add to the macaroni and cheese.
Put into casserole bowl.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Mix as listed in order.
I omit raisins.
Bake 2 hours at 275° or until done.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: In small mixing bowl combine egg, milk, chocolate-flavored syrup and cooking oil.
Beat mixture until well combined.
Place the pancake mix in medium mixing bowl.
Add the chocolate mixture and beat just until combined.
Pour about half the batter onto the grids of a preheated, lightly greased waffle baker.
Sprinkle with half of the chopped pecans.
Close waffle baker lid quickly and do not open while baking.
Remove baked waffle with a fork.
Repeat with remaining batter and nuts.
Stir together 1/4 cup chocolate syrup and maple-flavored syrup; serve with waffles.
Top with butter, if desired.
Makes two (9-inch) waffles.

title: chicken and crescent almandine
directions: In large saucepan combine first eight ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring to keep from sticking to pot, until mixture is hot and bubbly; pour into ungreased 8x12
baking dish.
(Water chestnuts should be drained and sliced.)
Separate crescent dough into two rectangles.
Place rectangles over hot mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread over dough.
Bake 20-25 minutes at 375° until crust is deep golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: emily's delite
directions: Combine cottage cheese, dry jello, 1/2 can mandarin oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Put in dish.
Decorate top with remaining orange slices.

title: diet soup
directions: Can cook celery and onions in clear water and freeze half for another time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook ingredients until done.
Can also freeze in containers.

title: crunchy turkey salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Blend in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Chill. Serve on salad greens.
Chicken may also be used.

title: rye cracker spread
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sauce.
Finely chop radishes.
Chop onions.
Stir into cream mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serve on rye crackers.

title: gingerbread cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add spices and molasses.
Stir in flour.
Chill.
Roll 1/4-inch thick. Cut out cookies.
Bake 13 minutes on greased baking sheet. Decorate.

title: divinity
directions: In glass 8-cup measure, cook sugar, syrup and water 6 minutes on High.
Stir, repeat.
Combine salt and egg whites, beat until stiff.
Slowly add syrup to eggs while beating until dull.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: easy elegant chicken
directions: Debone as many chicken breasts as needed.
Place dried beef under each chicken breast (2 to 3 layers of dried beef) then wrap chicken breast and dried beef in bacon.
Place in baking dish and pour over the top a mixture of sour cream and cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 300° for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: pork vegetable pie
directions: In a large
skillet
cook
pork
and onions; drain well. Stir in
spinach,
potatoes,
corn, mushrooms, thyme, rosemary, salt and pepper
until
mixed
well.
Add cheese and one beaten egg; spoon mixture into
a
10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll out pastry to 1 1/2-inch larger than baking dish.
Place pastry over filling and seal to edge of dish.
Flute.
Brush remaining egg over crust.
Bake
at 400° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add mashed bananas, flour and soda.
Mix in flavoring and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan, in slow oven, (300° to 325°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: holiday carrot bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water mixed with 1 teaspoon honey.
Beat together the oil, 1/2 cup honey and eggs (measure oil first, then honey).
Combine dry ingredients and beat in.
Add carrots.
Mix. Mix some of the flour with the nuts and fruit, then stir into the batter.
Pour into a well-oiled and floured pan (shake until flour coats the pan), and set in a warm place to rise for half an hour, covered with a cloth.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 55 minutes, or until a knife comes out clean.

title: mexican posole
directions: Cut pork into small cubes.
Brown on all sides in large skillet.
Add onions and saute until golden brown.
Add tomatoes, hominy and green chilies.
Mix gently.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
May cook uncovered for 30 minutes to reduce liquid, if desired.
Yields 18 to 20 servings.

title: colcannon
directions: Cover potatoes with cold water; add salt and pepper and boil until tender.
Drain well and shake pan over heat to dry potatoes out.
Mash and set aside.
Core and shred cabbage.
Boil in 2 cups salted water until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook. Drain well and toss with 2 tablespoons melted butter, cover loosely.
Chop scallions or leeks.
Pour milk in saucepan, add the scallions or leeks and bring to a boil.
Pour milk mixture into the mashed potatoes, adding a bit of salt and pepper.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in cabbage and heat over low heat, adding more milk, if needed.
Mound the mixture in a heated bowl, make a well in center, add butter and some minced fresh parsley.

title: homestyle sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Trim excess fat from spareribs and cut into 2-inch lengths. Put a large, heavy frying pan or a wok over high heat.
Sprinkle about a teaspoon of salt into it.
When the pan is hot, add half the spareribs.
The ribs will brown in their own fat.
Stir the ribs around so they won't burn; they should be brown on all sides within 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, vanilla and egg in a large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: mystery rolls
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon in small muffin tins. Bake until brown. This mixture will be very soft. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 rolls.

title: easy green rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Pour chicken broth in baking dish. Add 1/2 can of water.
Pour in rice, parsley and sauteed onion. Mix.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Check at 45 minutes for overcooking.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook sausage, onion and pepper until sausage browns.
Drain well.
Add cheese and 4 beaten eggs.
Cook until eggs are set. Put filling in shells; add sauce.
Fold.

title: pizza breakfast
directions: Flatten rolls in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Cook and drain sausage.
Pour crumbled sausage over rolls.
Mix together eggs, sauces and milk and pour over sausage.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
(May be prepared the night before.
Just refrigerate and cook in the morning.)

title: julie's dill dip
directions: Blend ingredients well and refrigerate for at least an hour. Great with veggies.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Coat an 8-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Dip chicken in egg whites and turn to coat.
