Mix breadcrumbs with Italian seasoning and dip chicken in breadcrumb mixture.
Turn to coat thoroughly.
Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken Cook until lightly browned and no longer pink inside (about 4 min. per side).
Place on paper towels to drain. Pour 1/2 c. of sauce evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheeses and bake until bubbly, about 25 min.

title: tabbuli(parsley salad)
directions: Soak wheat for approximately 1/2 hour.
Wash first.
Chop all the vegetables as fine as possible.
All except the tomatoes can be chopped in a blender by adding water, then draining.
Pour the olive oil and the lemon juice over the mixture and mix well.
This can be served over lettuce, cabbage or fresh grape leaves.
Or stuff cherry tomatoes with this mixture.

title: chicken alla cacciatore con polenta
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry with paper towel.
Heat oil in butter in Dutch oven.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; brown well on all sides.
Remove as browned and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to pan.
Saute until golden brown (15 minutes).
Add parsley, tomato, salt, basil and pepper.
Mix well, mashing tomatoes with fork.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add browned chicken and wine.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes, 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Make Polenta.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat the vinegar & water to boiling.
Add the mustard, salt & sugar.
Blend until mixed and let boil again.
Then pour over the combined celery seed, beets & onion.
Cover and place in the refrigerator to marinate overnight or longer.
Serve cold.

title: tina's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Roll in pecans.
Makes 1 large or 3 small cheese balls.
Freezes well.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add milk; add salt to sifted flour.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check with toothpick, when clean, cake is done.

title: coffee cake
directions: Bring to a
boil
raisins, coffee and shortening.
Take off heat and
let cool.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for one hour at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in dry container.
Add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Chill.
Better if you make it the night before.

title: soft beef tacos
directions: Cook beef in large skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until cooked through and brown (about 5 minutes). Stir in 2 cups tomatoes, cumin and oregano. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in 1 1/2 cups water. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until most of liquid has evaporated (about 20 minutes). Wrap tortillas in a clean kitchen towel. Microwave until hot (about 2 minutes).

title: glass candy
directions: Mix in pan. Cook to hard-crack stage. Remove from heat. Add food coloring and 1 1/2 teaspoons desired flavoring. Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Cool and break into pieces.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; toss and chill.

title: vermicelli or spaghetti with tomato anchovy sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, anchovies and capers.
Simmer 10 minutes (you may add fresh basil or oregano).
Cook spaghetti al dente.
Arrange on large platter. Spoon sauce over top.
Decorate with olives, cherry tomatoes and parsley.
Season with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake the devil's food cake as directed in sheet cake pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Put half of cake in bottom of large bowl.
Put half of vanilla pudding, then half of chocolate pudding, 1 container of Cool Whip and 1/2 of the crumbled Skor bars.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix tuna, peas, soup and milk with half of cheese.
Add macaroni.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add carrots and pineapple and refrigerate until set for serving.

title: carrot cake(without grated carrots)
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.

Cream eggs, sugar, carrots and oil until smooth and creamy; add vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture, then nuts, raisins and pineapple. Bake in greased tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and slice strawberries.
Put into cooked pie shell. Save a few strawberries for top of pie.
Cook sugar, syrup, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add food coloring and jello.
Pour this over the strawberries.
Let set.
When cooled, add Cool Whip and a few strawberries for decoration.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oyster crackers.
Place oyster crackers in large Ziploc bag.
Pour dressing mixture over crackers and shake gently.
Let set for a day or two, shaking gently several times.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks only one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour until all is well mixed.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to mixture.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into pie crust shell, then drizzle syrup on top of pie.
Swirl with a spoon.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: marinated baby carrots
directions: Arrange whole carrots in a vegetable steamer.
Cover and steam over boiling water until just tender when pierced (10-12 minutes).
Plunge into cold water to cool quickly; then drain. Arrange carrots vertically in a clean 1-pint jar that is about the same height as carrots.
Tuck in bay leaves.
In a bowl, stir together vinegar, water, sugar, salt, mustard seeds, dill weed, red pepper, dill seeds, and garlic until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over carrots, cover tightly, and refrigerate for at least 2 days or up to 3 weeks.
Makes 1 pint.

title: grape-nuts roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in well buttered loaf pan or casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May be served with gravy or mushroom sauce.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples into buttered baking dish.
Sift together sugar and flour; blend until mixture is crumbly.
Pour 1/2 cup of cider or apple juice over apples.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and crumb mixture over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until topping is slightly brown.

title: chiso rice
directions: Mix well together in rice cooker and cook.

title: baked rabbit
directions: Roll the rabbit pieces in the complete pancake flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in the margarine.
Combine the bouillon and water. Pour over the rabbit.
Slice the onion over top.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: layer dinner
directions: Arrange ingredients in layers in a greased casserole.
Water to keep moist, about 1 cup.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: maple syrup cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together the cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients and combine until well blended.
Pour batter into a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until firm in the center and golden on the edges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes; slice while still hot.
Add onion, celery, eggs and bacon.
Leave bacon drippings in skillet; add sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Heat and pour over potato mixture.
Serve hot.

title: boston cream cupcakes
directions: Using cake mix, make cupcakes following box directions.
Allow cupcakes to cool.
Make vanilla pudding using box directions.
Cut an X in middle of cupcakes.
Pipe vanilla pudding into cup cakes. Frost filled cupcakes with chocolate frosting.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Mix black pepper, garlic cloves and salt with olive oil.
Wash cut up chicken, dry and rub with pepper, salts, garlic and oil mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sunflower seed potato patties
directions: Blend all ingredients except wheat germ.
Mixture should be firm. Shape into patties. Coat with wheat germ. Arrange on oiled cookie sheet and broil until golden brown on each side.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coney sauce
directions: In skillet brown beef.
Break with fork until fine; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: best turkey dressing
directions: Melt butter and fry with celery and onion on low for short time.
Cut bread into small pieces, put in large bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered. Remove cover and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: zucchini-rice stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and add remaining ingredients except soup.
Cook on top of stove for a few minutes.
For a casserole or hot dish, add mushroom soup.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9-inch glass pie dish. Layer remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: thick crust pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco until soft. Add gradually the sugar and eggs one at a time. Sift flour and baking powder and add to Crisco mixture alternately with milk. Add flavoring. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: picante dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips of your choice.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread in square pan (13 x 9-inch).
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and remaining 3 eggs together.
Spread over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and butter.
Dip chicken in butter and roll into mixture.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: broccoli n' rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients in a bowl. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine cookies and sugar.
Blend in butter.
Stir in orange juice concentrate, vanilla and nuts.
Shape into balls and shake in bag with powdered sugar.
Arrange in single layer and refrigerate overnight.
Yield:
36 to 40 balls.

title: skillet chops with rice
directions: In skillet, brown chops; pour off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup, water, celery and thyme.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover; cook 20 minutes longer or until chops and rice are tender.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat water, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and sauerkraut to dissolve the sugar.
Combine celery, green pepper, onion and pimento.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Fold in yogurt. Refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chili verde(hot picante sauce)
directions: Blend together in blender.
Cook in covered pan over medium heat until it loses its green color (about 1 hour).
Makes 1 quart. Keep in refrigerator in covered jar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Combine with ground meat and remaining ingredients except tortillas. Make alternate layers of tortillas and meat sauce in baking dish beginning with tortillas.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Unroll 1 can of rolls; press into a lightly greased 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: marinated london broil
directions: In a flat glass baking dish combine the garlic, ginger, allspice, thyme, mustard, bay leaf and Worcestershire.
Add the meat and rub the marinade over the surface.
Marinate for 1/2 hour, turning the meat once.
Grill meat until done, 8 minutes on each side for rare.
Carve into thin slices and serve.
Serves 4.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and butter to form fine crumbs. Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Take 1 cup sour milk and add soda and stir.
Add beaten egg and mix with dry mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili powder.
Put on wax paper and make a roll.
Put chili powder on wax paper and roll cheese in it. Refrigerate.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Pour melted butter over cubed bread.
Beat eggs with sugar. Add large can crushed pineapple (juice and all).
Mix and pour over cubed bread.
Place in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half and remove yolk.
Mash yolks; add crabmeat, relish, mustard and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff eggs.
Garnish with pimento strips or sliced stuffed olives.

title: orange sherbet fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: carnation's failure proof gravy
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet on low heat.
Blend in flour and salt until smooth (2 to 3 minutes).

title: light italian vinaigrette
directions: In a tightly covered container, shake all ingredients.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook shrimp and set aside.
Add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in the oil.
Cook until wilted.
Add tomato paste and cook 15 minutes.
Add water, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat about 40 minutes more.
Add shrimp and cornstarch.
Cook about 5 minutes more.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients and coat pretzels.
Spread on large baking sheet and bake at 200° for 40 minutes, stirring every ten minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and spread over crust.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Cut carrots crosswise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cook, covered, until just tender.
Drain.
Then combine honey, cornstarch, salt and ginger in a small saucepan.
Add orange juice.
Cook and stir constantly until bubbly and thick.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots, stirring to coat evenly.
Garnish with parsley.

title: grandma white's cranberry conserve
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until berries burst and are soft. Add sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add nuts and chill.

title: rigatoni with broccoli parmesan
directions: Prepare rigatoni according to box or microwave directions. Boil, steam or microwave broccoli until tender.
(Cut up if pieces are large.)
Toss rigatoni, broccoli and margarine together. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on mixture to taste.
Season with fresh ground pepper.
Serve with Italian bread and salad.
(Do not invite President Bush.) Serves 3 to 4.

title: coffee ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream slightly.
Press half of the ice cream into cookie pie shell.
Top with whole jar of fudge sauce (do not heat). Add the rest of the ice cream, mounding it up.
Press sliced almonds all over top of pie; putting the pie on a cookie sheet is less messy.
Freeze immediately.
Work quickly so ice cream doesn't run all over.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Wash and slice a combination of the first 8 ingredients. Spray 11 x 13 pan with butter Pam.	Layer vegetables.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All and cheese.
Melt butter and mix with crackers; put on top.
Bake at 350° until crackers are brown.
(Check at 30 minutes; could take up to 1 hour.)

title: low-fat sausage quiche
directions: Combine egg, Egg Beaters, milk and salt.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese pastry in lined pie pan.
Pour milk and egg mixture into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: layered vegetable salad(24-hour)
directions: Place lettuce in flat bottom round salad bowl.
Layer onions, celery, pepper, carrots, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, bacon, peas and eggs over lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Pimiento may be added for garnish.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix
melted
margarine	and
graham
cracker crumbs and press into a 13 x 9-inch dish or pan. Chill 20 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Spread 1/2 mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 6 minutes; remove from oven and cool at least 2 minutes.
Melt caramel candy with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour mixture over cake.
Drop chocolate chips over caramel mixture.
Mix 1/2 cup chopped nuts with remaining cake mix and drop by spoonfuls over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over mixture and bake 18 minutes.
Let set overnight before cutting.

title: bourbon-pecan pound cake
directions: Beat shortening in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Combine sour cream and bourbon; add to creamed mixture alternately with flour mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 to 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Drizzle glaze over cake, if desired.

title: sour cream rhubarb squares
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Add flour and salt alternately with sour cream.
Stir in rhubarb.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: In mixing bowl A, work Psalms to a cream together with Jeremiah.
Add 6 well-beaten Isaiah. Slowly stir in Matthew.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in 10 x 10-inch pan and melt.
Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk until blended.
Pour onto melted oleo, but do not mix.
Pour fruit with syrup over all.
Place in oven 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly and spoon off excess fat.
Mix with spaghetti sauce.

title: oregano rice
directions: Cook onion and raw rice in the oleo over a medium flame for 5 minutes (do not brown).
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into a casserole; cover tightly and bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Serve with ham, fried chicken or steak.

title: rice krispie peanut butter bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cool chicken breasts and cut into small pieces. Toast almonds and sesame seeds. Combine with remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain the broccoli.
Put the broccoli in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup and evaporated milk with a whisk until smooth.
Pour over the broccoli.
Mix water, butter and stuffing.
Put on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: california fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello with spatula.
Night before, drain canned fruit.
Then add fruit to first two ingredients.
Just before serving, add partially softened Cool Whip.
Serve with plain cake or use with other salads.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine until well blended.
Pour and spread into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 egg, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over the top of the cake mixture and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: meat with red stuff
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Place in greased iron skillet. Salt and pepper potatoes. Place chopped onion over potatoes.
Press uncooked ground chuck over onion and potatoes. Press down evenly and seal to sides of skillet.
Pour tomato soup over ground chuck.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Mix Ranch dressing, canola oil, red pepper and garlic powder together. Pour over crackers. Keep turned and covered. Will keep a long time.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in 1 3/4-quart casserole dish.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs.
Stir in corn, milk and salt.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: codfish salad
directions: Soak codfish overnight; boil and bone. (Watch out for small bones.)
Cut onions into small bits and slice the stuffed olives. Cut up the avocado.
Now mix and place the tomatoes and avocado around the fish in the center of a favorite pretty plate and decorate with lettuce.
Also boil the bananas and place decoratively around the plate.

title: broccoli mushroom lasagna
directions: Spread about 1/2 cup of Creamed Mushrooms in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer noodles (seasoned with pepper), broccoli, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, remaining Creamed Mushrooms and Parmesan cheese 3 times.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before cutting into servings. Serves 6.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Bring soups, Ro-Tel and broth to a boil.
Saute onion and add to soup mixture.
After soup mixture comes to boil, add chicken and heat through.

Grease a baking dish; then start with chips on bottom, then soup mixture and continue doing this until soup mixture is gone, being sure you end with soup mixture on top. Place in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then place cheese on top and cook until cheese melts and casserole is bubbling.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt, spices, lemon rind and oleo.
Toss apples in mixture.
Arrange in pie shell.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° in oven for 25 minutes or until crisp on top.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Add undiluted soups.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add noodles to meat mixture.
Fold into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Butter casserole dish; put in cubed bread, then grated cheese, then bacon.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Pour over bread, cheese and bacon.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (great for brunch).

title: banana cheesecake dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper in frying pan with butter. When brown, add flour.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and 1 cup grated cheese.
Mix and pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle over cup of cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let set about 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: acorn squash bake
directions: Cut squash in half.
Remove pits.
Place in pot.
Cover with water.
Boil on stove top until done.
Scoop squash from the shell.
In a bowl, mix squash, margarine, sugar and heavy cream together.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: plum pudding
directions: Steam in double boiler for 5 hours.

title: oven fried cornmeal catfish
directions: Defrost fish, if frozen.
Spray a nonstick pan until slick with cooking spray.
Sprinkle cornmeal on plate.
Fork whip egg, oil and lemon juice together in another dish.
Dip fish in the egg mixture, then the crumbs, coating both sides.
Arrange fish in a single layer on the nonstick pan.
Place the pan on the bottom shelf and bake at 475° for about 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily and is golden brown.

title: chocolate vanilla pudding
directions: Scald 2 1/2 cups milk in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add remaining milk to make a smooth paste. Add some of the hot milk to the paste and mix thoroughly.
Then add the paste to hot milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks and add some of the hot pudding, then add egg yolks to mixture and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Chill thoroughly and top with meringue.

title: frosted chews
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and syrup. Turn off heat. Add the peanut butter and stir. Add the Special K, half at a time. Stir well.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread on bars.
Let harden before serving.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Unroll one package crescent rolls and place in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread over dough; unroll other package rolls and place over mixture.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon over top and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber chips
directions: Slice and wash cukes.
Mix with peppers, onion and salt.
Bury in ice for 3 hours and drain.
Mix vinegar, water, turmeric, cloves, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar in a large pan, heating.
Add drained cucumber; mix and simmer until transparent. Pack in jars, boiling hot, to within 1/4-inch of top and seal.

title: banana muffins
directions: In a bowl, cream margarine with sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and mashed bananas.
In another bowl, stir together flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat into banana mixture, then stir in chocolate chips (if using).
Turn batter into greased and floured muffin tins or use paper liners.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool on a rack.

title: rhubarb marshmallow creme torte
directions: Combine flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cook rhubarb with a little water.
While cooking, add sugar; boil up like a sauce, then add strawberry jello.
Let cool, then spread over crust and refrigerate to set.
Add mini marshmallows to Cool Whip and spread over rhubarb.
Next, mix vanilla pudding as directed and spread over cream layer.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grease	a
quart baking dish.
Preheat oven to 400°. Brown ground chuck, pepperoni, pepper and onion.	Drain grease off.
In casserole
dish, mix oregano, soups, milk, mushrooms and
cheese, but
reserve
cheese.	Add meat mixture and noodles.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Spread coconut and nuts over the top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: rum lime mousses
directions: In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over the rum and let soften for 1 minute.
Stir in lime juice, zest, yolks and 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Cook mixture over low heat until thickened.
Set pan in bowl of ice to cool, but do not let set.
Beat egg whites with a pinch of salt until they hold soft peaks.
Beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar until whites hold stiff peaks.
Pour 1/4 of white mixture into lime mixture.
Fold in remaining whites gently.
Beat cream until stiff peaks form.
Fold into lime mixture with green food coloring.
Chill.
Spoon into dessert dishes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck in frying pan sprayed with Pam.
Add onions and peppers and cook until tender.
Transfer to a large pot.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer until heated through.

title: peach slush
directions: You will need a blender.
Combine peaches, milk or cream, sugar or artificial sweetener and vanilla extract in blender. After placing ingredients in blender, set blender speed on pulverize and turn on.
Add crushed ice a little at a time into top middle entrance of blender cap.
Blender time should be about 20 seconds.
Pour out into tall glasses.
Hits the spot on a hot summer day.

title: zauner krapfen(austrian nut butter cookie)
directions: Blend butter into other ingredients using spoon.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Roll out on floured pastry cloth or board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into round with 2 1/4-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes, until light golden brown.

These cookies are delicious plain or made into a sandwich cookie, filling with a Chocolate Buttercream Frosting. The Austrian manner is to spread the top of sandwich with a thin jam and dribble a chocolate icing on top.
Then sprinkle with slivered almonds.

title: diabetic banana nut bread
directions: Sprinkle sugar over bananas and stir; blend in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; add to bananas.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer until bread is done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand 15 minutes.
Drop, using a teaspoon, into 340° grease.
Cook until a golden brown.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine slightly beaten eggs with muffin mix and both cans of corn; mix well.
Add sour cream and melted butter or margarine. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in thick boiler.
After it comes to a boil, boil it 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl over the chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add the chopped pecans and butter; stir.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Cut into squares after it cools.

title: basil-lemon sauce
directions: Add ingredients to a food processor or blender and pulsate until just combined.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cream of tartar to boil. Break crackers in 4 pieces each; put crackers in deep dish pie crust. Pour liquid mixture over crackers. Sprinkle with cinnamon and place pats of butter over pie. Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cinnamon pecan breakfast rolls
directions: Grease an angel food or Bundt pan.
Drop frozen rolls into pan.
Mix dry pudding mix, pecans, brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; sprinkle over frozen rolls.
Cut butter into small pieces; arrange over mixture.
Cover with foil; let stand overnight.

title: strawberry breakfast
directions: Put
rusks
in loaf pan.
In blender puree strawberries with Equal.
Add
Jell-O and boiling water.
Blend in cottage cheese. Makes 5 breakfasts.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels in cream in top of double boiler.
Cool slightly. Make crumb mixture of flour, butter, oatmeal, salt, soda and brown sugar.
Press 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom of 11 x 7 baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over baked crumb mixture.
Carefully spread caramel mixture over chips and nuts.
Sprinkle with rest of crumb mixture and press down.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Chill and cut in bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: zak's flapjaks
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together in a large bowl. Whisk eggs and buttermilk until smooth in another bowl. Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, along with melted butter. Let batter rest for 10 minutes. Heat large skillet over medium-high heat until hot and melt 1 teaspoon butter in pan. Spoon batter into skillet for each Flapjak. Cook until bubbles form on surface. Turn Flapjaks and cook other side until golden brown. Batter makes about 18 Flapjaks.

title: apple-cream-black walnut pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add sour cream, vanilla, black walnut flavoring, apples, egg and walnuts.
Stir all together well and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except hash browns in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until cheese is melted, then add hash browns and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Top with crushed corn flakes cereal.

title: vegetarian el paso rice pilaf
directions: In a heavy 2-quart pot, saute onions in olive oil for 1 minute over high heat, stirring.
Add rice, lentils, pimento, kidney beans, corn, broth, salsa, garlic powder and chili powder.
Stir to blend.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add bread crumbs, milk, salt and mustard. Add browned drained sausage; top with cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until center is set.
Let set for a few minutes before cutting. Casserole is better if you mix the night before and refrigerate before cooking.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white; add water until frothy.
Add pecans and mix until all nuts are covered with egg white.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add nuts and cook.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Very good.

title: real potato soup
directions: Combine broth and potatoes, and cook for 20 minutes until potatoes are cooked through.
As potatoes are cooking saute onions in a pan sprayed with cooking spray. Then add onions, mushrooms, and bacon to potatoes.
When potatoes are soft stir in cheese and sour cream.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Thicken with flour mixture.
One serving is one cup.

title: smoky tuna potage
directions: Blend soup and water in 2-quart saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika.
Mix.
Cover pan and simmer 10 or 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pear preserves
directions: Boil 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Add pears and sliced lemon.
Cook 15 more minutes.
Add remaining sugar and water.
Cook until pears are clear and thick.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Simmer chicken in small amount of oil with pepper and onion. Salt and pepper to taste.
When chicken is done, add corn and salsa and rice and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes until rice is fluffy.
Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: country franks
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook frank slices until lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove to bowl.
In same skillet over medium heat in hot salad oil cook peppers and onions, oregano, salt and pepper until tender, stirring frequently.
Add franks and tomato sauce.
Toss gently together; heat through.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool thoroughly.

title: pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish. Layer potatoes and place pork chops on top of the potatoes. Mix together broth soups and water. Pour on top of pork chops. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Fry out sausage, stirring with fork to crumble.
Do not brown, cook till pink is gone (drain).
Mix with other ingredients.
Add enough water to make a dough.
Roll into ball.
Flatten slightly before baking on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Freeze!

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour with soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and walnuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, depending on oven; watch carefully. Yields 70 to 80 cookies.

title: swedish molasses cookies
directions: Beat egg,
add
molasses,
sugar,
shortening and soda. Beat until mixed.
Sift
together flour, salt and spices.
Add gradually, blending well.
Chill several hours.
Roll out thin (1/16-inch). Cut out and bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla, then add melted margarine.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Yields 1 pie.

title: cherry jello
directions: Let jello almost set, then add pecans and cherries.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain and add remaining ingredients except Doritos.
Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Crumble Doritos on top.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese. Chop cheese.
Add a little at a time until it melts.
Serve hot with chips.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, blend all base ingredients until crumbly.
Press mixture into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Drop spoonfuls into small amount of hot oil in skillet.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel a minute.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and seasonings. Stir in onions, spinach, water chestnuts and red peppers. Cover.
Refrigerate to blend flavors. Serve with crisp vegetable dippers, assorted crackers or bread.
Serve in hollowed out round bread.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients as given.
Put in 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt Butter in large saucepan.
Stir in Brown Sugar.
Remove from heat.
Let cool about 10 minutes.
Sift together and set aside Flour, Baking Powder, and Salt.
Beat Eggs into Sugar Mixture, one at a time.
Add Instant Pudding and mix well.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Add Chocolate Chips and Nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: quick and easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Turn mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake about 45 minutes in a 325 degree oven.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix egg, sugar and flour.
Add juices and cook until thick. Let cool and pour over fruit.
Mix.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onions and celery until meat is brown and
onion
is
tender;
drain.
Combine
all
other ingredients, except
bacon
bits.
Stir
into ground beef mixture. Pour into
large baking pan.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. Cover. Bake at 350°
for
hour and 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 12 cups.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Coat chicken breasts with flour and add to pan.
Lightly brown chicken on one side.
Turn over and cook breasts until tender.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on each breast.
Cover and cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve over Uncle Ben's wild rice prepared to package directions.

title: orange shortbread squares
directions: In small bowl, combine 2 c. flour, baking powder and salt. In large bowl beat margarine and 1/2 c. sugar until light and fluffy.
At low speed, gradually stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Chill 2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine liquid Coffee-mate and remaining ingredients; mix gently but thoroughly.
Place in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for 60 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: mushroom cream cheese logs
directions: Drain chopped mushrooms.
Mix and blend well with cream cheese and seasoned salt.
Roll crescent rolls out onto a baking sheet, forming a rectangle.
Press together at seams.
Beginning at the small end, spread filling along 2/3 of the rectangle.
Again, beginning at the small end of the rectangle, gently roll crescent rolls into a roll and pinch together at end.
Cut roll into 1 1/2-inch pieces; brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake on an ungreased sheet at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Cook onion and sausage in skillet until brown.
Prepare cornbread and pour half of batter in a deep skillet.
Drain grease from sausage and onions.
Put sausage mixture on top of half the cornbread mixture.
Pour corn, then cheese over the sausage.
Add remaining cornbread batter and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bread is browned.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add Ricotta cheese, flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Oil and season chicken (may use McCormick chicken seasoning).
Lay on top of rice mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked cream cheese(appetizer)
directions: Sprinkle dill on block of cream cheese.
Leave crescent rolls in one piece.
Wrap cream cheese in crescent rolls.
Place on cookie sheet, seam side down.
Brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350°.

title: shortbread
directions: Note:
If you can't get rice flour, use 4 cups all-purpose flour, total.
